 ('145', '232', 'en_us', 'The Rainmaking Sessions - Fostering a corporate innovation culture', '<p>Large banks and corporations operate in a risk adverse environment, where products are often built in silos by teams with entrenched cultures and procedures. This is often at odds with the fail fast and pivot mindset of the lean startup methodology of developing innovative products and services. How can large corporates create an innovation culture that includes the enterprise? How can management empower the ‘Yes, ands..’ within teams to lead and convince the ‘No, buts…’ of the benefits of an entrepreneurial innovation culture?</p>\n\n<p><em>Fostering an internal innovation culture </em>will be an interactive, think tank style roundtable where you can hear from industry experts to debate and discuss the current state of the industry as well as future trends with your peers.\n\n</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>You will hear from:\n\n</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Rachael Jackson, Solutions, Design, Services, RBS\n\n</li><li>Alex Farcet, partner at Rainmaking Innovation\n\n<ul><li>Moderation – Liz Lumley\n\n</li></ul></li></ul><p>Please join us at the Rainmaking Loft to be a part of the Summer Season series of thought provoking Rainmaking Sessions looking at innovation and disruptive trends.\n\n</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<ul><li>When: 26 May 2016\n\n</li><li>Where: The Rainmaking Loft, 1 St Katherine’s Way, London E1W 4UN\n\n</li><li>Agenda:\n\n</li></ul><ul><li>o   8:15 - Arrival at loft for coffee\n\n</li><li>o   8:30 – Buffet style breakfast served\n\n</li><li>o   8:45 - Welcome and talks begin\n\n</li><li>o   9:15 - Moderated Roundtable starts\n\n</li><li>o   10:30 - Breakfast Roundtable ends\n\n</li></ul><p>Spaces are limited, so please RSVP by 23 May 2016 with Cilia Li at <a href=\"mailto:cilia@startupbootcamp.org\" target=\"_blank\">cilia@startupbootcamp.org</a> for your chance to be a part of this special event.\n\n</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Once you reserve your place, please shout about your attendance by sharing ‘I will be adding my views and insights to the #RainmakingSessions on <em>Fostering an internal innovation culture</em> on 26 May 2016!’ on your social media channels.\n\n</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>The Rainmaking Sessions – the Summer Season.</p>\n\n<p>The Rainmaking Sessions are series of monthly, breakfast roundtables to foster debate, discussion and discourse on the nature of innovation in corporates, FinTech, InsurTech, Digital Health and Smart Transportation.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/the-rainmaking-sessions-fostering-a-corporate-innovation-culture-tickets-25197718053', 'Rainmaking Loft - London', '1 St Katherine’s Way, London E1W 4UN', '2016-11-24 17:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-10-26 17:04:48', '2016-10-27 08:23:58', '12dc3e1f-33cb-4348-a597-ab9ad28159c7'),
