 ('158', '245', 'en_us', 'The Rainmaking Sessions  - Innovation in the financial supply chain', '<p>Innovation in the financial supply chain – <em>How can banks find opportunities for innovation in the changing face of the supply chain?</em></p><p>In the post-digital, global economy, corporate and commercial clients are both importers and exporters; supply chains are deeper and more fragmented and access to trade credit is being squeezed. The International Chamber of Commerce (ICC) Standard Definitions for Techniques of Supply Chain Finance pave the way for greater adoption and commonality in supply chain finance and bank assisted open account offerings.</p><p>Supply chains for many of your corporate clients are multi-layered and complex, with difficulties in obtaining visibility, connectivity or sufficient risk information across all parties involved. Visibility of the so-called “long tail” is crucial for reducing transaction risk. In many areas, supply chains are getting shorter and they need to be dynamic, fast, agile and data-centric. The emergence of cloud platforms, new marketplaces, eDocs and new standards now provide the ecosystem for banks and new entrants to revolutionise the market. But collaboration is king.</p><p><em>Innovation in the financial supply chain</em>, will be an interactive, think tank style roundtable, sponsored by Misys. Industry experts and supply chain professionals will debate and discuss the current state of the industry as well as future trends.Please join us at the Rainmaking Loft to be a part of this series of thought-provoking Rainmaking Sessions, on trends that are shaping our industry.</p><p>You will hear from:</p>\n\n<ul><li>Tom Ward, Head of Finance - Supply Chain at Tesco PLC</li><li>Mike Walker, Head of Product Management, Open Account &amp; Supply Chain Finance, </li></ul><p>MisysAgenda:</p>\n\n<ul><li>8:15 - Arrival at loft for coffee </li><li>8:30 – Buffet style breakfast served </li><li>8:45 - Welcome and talks begin </li><li>9:15 - Moderated Roundtable starts </li><li>10:30 - Breakfast Roundtable endsSpaces are limited, so please register for your chance to be a part of this special event.</li></ul><p>The Rainmaking Sessions\n<em>The Rainmaking Sessions are series of monthly, breakfast roundtables to foster debate, discussion and discourse on the nature of innovation in corporates, FinTech, InsurTech, Digital Health and Smart Transportation.</em></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/innovation-in-the-financial-supply-chain-tickets-28785655671', 'Rainmaking Loft - London', '1 St. Katherine\'s Way, London, E1W 1UN', '2016-12-07 08:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-10-27 12:10:20', '2016-11-15 18:02:19', 'acb724d3-f524-4337-a0c4-7c2eea6122bb'),
 ('159', '246', 'en_us', 'The Rainmaking Sessions - Disruptive InsurTech: From now to 2030', '<p>For years FinTech has dominating with news of investments, advancements and innovation. However, the industry on everyone’s radar for 2016 is insurance. In order to examine these developments, Rainmaking Innovations, in association with Startupbootcamp InsurTech, invite you to an exclusive breakfast roundtable event looking at digital disruption in insurance.</p><p><em>Disruptive InsurTech: From now to 2030 - What will your path to success be?</em> will be an interactive, think tank style roundtable where you can hear from industry experts to debate and discuss the current state of the industry as well as future trends with your peers.</p><p>You will hear from:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Sabine VanderLinden, MD Startupbootcamp InsurTech</li><li>Carolina Vicente, Director of Digital Marketing, Google</li><li>Moderated by: Liz Lumley, Rainmaking Innovation</li></ul><p>Please join us at the Rainmaking Loft to be a part of the first of a series of thought provoking Rainmaking Sessions looking at innovation and disruptive trends.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>When: 28 October 2016</li><li>Where: The Rainmaking Loft, 1 St Katherine’s Way, London E1W 4UN</li><li>Agenda:</li><li>9:00 - Arrival at loft for coffee</li><li>9:15 - Buffet style breakfast served</li><li>9:45 - Welcome and talks begin</li><li>10:15 - Moderated Roundtable starts</li><li>11:30 - Breakfast Roundtable ends</li></ul><p>Spaces are limited, so please RSVP for your chance to be a part of this special event. </p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[]', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/disruptive-insurtech-from-now-to-2030-registration-26699864012', 'Rainmaking Loft - London', '1 St. Katherine\'s Way, London, E1W 1UN', '2016-10-28 08:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-10-27 12:24:23', '2016-11-15