he region, we knew that the existing ecosystem would measure us on the basis of the value we displayed. To ensure our event attendees left with new insights, knowledge, and inspiration, we brought expertise, high-profile international mentors, and investors to our events.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"163\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"We designed and delivered a range of events to support and encourage local startups:\",\"text\":\"\\u2022 Two investment labs\\r\\n\\u2022 Two 48 hour hackathons\\r\\n\\u2022 Four women\\u2019s meetups\\r\\n\\u2022 Six mini bootcamps\\r\\n\\u2022 Three open offices\\r\\n\\u2022 Two job fairs\\r\\n\\u2022 Two investor pitch events\\r\\n\\u2022 One corporate matchmaking event\\r\\n\\u2022 A series of intensive, high impact workshops\\r\\n\",\"image\":[\"150\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"164\":{\"type\":\"imageBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"images\":[\"152\",\"153\",\"154\",\"155\"]}},\"165\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Over two years we hosted 27 events across Jordan, Egypt and Tunisia \",\"text\":\"+ 90 jobs created\\r\\n+ 820 entrepreneurs\\r\\n+ 70 partners\\r\\n+ 130 startups engaged\\r\\n+ 160 mentors engaged\\r\\n+ 10.000 in network\\r\\n\",\"backgroundColour\":\"white\"}}},\"72\":[\"147\"],\"67\":\"\",\"69\":\"\",\"68\":\"\",\"71\":\"\"}}', '2016-10-25 17:20:52', '2016-10-25 17:20:52', '7af7e347-a945-43db-b7cd-2084bf2d7a89'),
 ('59', '158', '4', '15', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Startup MENA: Empowering Entrepreneurship in the Middle East and North Africa\",\"slug\":\"startup-mena-empowering-entrepreneurs-in-the-middle-east-and-north-africa\",\"postDate\":1477415700,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"156\"],\"47\":{\"159\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"In 2014, we partnered with The Danish Foreign Ministry to deliver a 2 year program stimulating economic growth in the private sectors of Egypt, Jordan and Tunisia. \",\"image\":[\"147\"]}},\"160\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Seeding a Startup Ecosystem\",\"text\":\"Since 2003 The Danish government has been actively collaborating with the Middle East and North Africa to strengthen their dialogue and cooperation to support the ongoing reform and democratization of the region.\\r\\n\\r\\nHowever, political revolution and unemployment still threaten to impede the successful democratization process in some countries in the region. Stimulating job creation has therefore become a key objective for The Danish-Arab Partnership Program across the region. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"161\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"In 2014, high rates of unemployment continued, particularly amongst young people, despite many being well-educated, ready to work and keen to actively help shape the future of their countries. \\r\\n\\r\\nIt was in this context that we were challenged to design and deliver a program with The Danish Foreign Ministry: creating jobs and growth through entrepreneurship.\",\"image\":[\"151\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"162\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Leading Through Value \",\"text\":\"As our team was new to the region, we knew that the existing ecosystem would measure us on the basis of the value we displayed. To ensure our event attendees left with new insights, knowledge, and inspiration, we brought in expertise, high-profile international mentors, and investors to all our events.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"163\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"We delivered a range of events to support and encourage local startups:\",\"text\":\"\\u2022 Two investment labs\\r\\n\\u2022 Two 48 hour hackathons\\r\\n\\u2022 Four women\\u2019s meetups\\r\\n\\u2022 Six mini bootcamps\\r\\n\\u2022 Three open offices\\r\\n\\u2022 Two job fairs\\r\\n\\u2022 Two investor pitch events\\r\\n\\u2022 One corporate matchmaking event\\r\\n\\u2022 A series of intensive, high impact workshops\\r\\n\",\"image\":[\"150\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"164\":{\"type\":\"imageBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"images\":[\"152\",\"153\",\"154\",\"155\"]}},\"165\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Over two years we hosted 27 events across Jordan, Egypt and Tunisia \",\"text\":\"+ 90 jobs created\\r\\n+ 820 entrepreneurs\\r\\n+ 70 partners\\r\\n+ 130 startups engaged\\r\\n+ 160 mentors engaged\\r\\n+ 10.000 in network\\r\\n\",\"backgroundColour\":\"white\"}}},\"72\":[\"147\"],\"67\":\"\",\"69\":\"\",\"68\":\"\",\"71\":\"\"}}', '2016-10-25 17:35:15', '2016-10-25 17:35:15', '455ebafe-2bde-4d1a-90a5-a40c07ff0fba'),
 ('60', '24', '4', '1', 'en_us', '8', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"How Danske Bank Entered the Startup World\",\"slug\":\"how-danske-bank-is-making-a-splash-in-the-startup-world\",\"postDate\":1477327740,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"23\"],\"47\":{\"121\":{\"type\":\"imageBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"images\":[\"54\",\"56\",\"93\",\"102\",\"104\"]}},\"42\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"We partnered with Danske Bank to create TheHub.dk, a platform that aims to relieve the pains of Danish startups and provide a platform for Danske Bank to engage with the startup ecosystem. \",\"image\":[\"37\"]}},\"43\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"A long term perspective on growth and support\",\"text\":\"Danske Bank came to us in the Fall of 2015 with an exciting challenge: to create and run a project that would add value to Danish startups and accelerate the growth of early stage companies.\\u00a0\\r\\n\\r\\nDanske Bank wanted to test new forms of engagement with emerging businesses. By actively participating in the Danish startup ecosystem, they can gain early insights into new technologies and business models that could impact their business in the future.\\r\\n\\r\\nBy supporting startups at an early stage, helping them succeed and grow, the bank would also create a wider stream of potential future customers.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"44\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"After over 100 founder interviews, we found three major pain points faced by Danish startups: \",\"text\":\"1. Recruitment: lack of a nationwide, startup focused job board \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Funding: navigating the overwhelming number of investors and funding options to find the right choice\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Knowledge Sharing: capitalizing on the experience of successful founders to accelerate progress\\r\\n\\r\\nWith these three problems in mind, we created The Hub.\\r\\n\",\"image\":[\"36\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"90\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"An online platform, community and resource center \",\"text\":\"Targeting recruitment first, we built a job board tailored specifically to startups. \\r\\n\\r\\nWe found that startups rely on their own networks and traditional job boards for hiring. But they were missing something fit for purpose. Specifically for entrepreneurs, targeting job seekers interested in joining startups.\\r\\n\\r\\nWe\\u2019ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits, converting to 600 weekly applications. This is paired with great feedback from both startups and applicants using the site. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"120\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"We\\u2019ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits, converting to 600 weekly applications.\\\"\",\"image\":[\"39\"]}},\"46\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"We received far more applications through the Hub compared to elsewhere. All the applicants were relevant and part of our target group. For those reasons, I would recommend the Hub (and have already done it)\\\"\",\"quoteName\":\"Happy Hub User\",\"role\":\"\",\"image\":[\"39\"]}},\"47\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"To help navigate the funding options available to Danish startups, our next solution was to create a tool which could match startups with the most relevant options for them, based on their industry, experience, level of maturity and team size. This included profiles of the top 50 investors in Denmark.\",\"image\":[\"35\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"48\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"Knowledge sharing posed the greatest challenge. The majority of the information startups need is topical, specific to their industry, stage and product. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe Hub therefore needed to address the need for both startup specific, and generic content. To achieve this, we\\u2019ve started to develop a mentor matching scheme to pair startups with relevant advisors. \\r\\n\\r\\nMeanwhile, we\\u2019ve also developed a number of tools to share best practices around some of the steps almost all startups follow.  From raising funds to gaining the very first customers.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"49\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Widening The Hub\\u2019s Reach\",\"text\":\"Today, the Hub is the largest startup recruitment site in Denmark. And, we\\u2019re now applying what we\\u2019ve learned across the Nordics, launching Hubs in Norway and Sweden, opening up opportunities for cross-country applications in markets where Danske Bank is most active.\",\"image\":[\"41\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"new1\":{\"type\":\"videoBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"youtubeVideoId\":\"c9Y0Zlm1Puc\"}}},\"72\":[\"35\"],\"67\":\"\\u201cWe have partnered with Rainmaking because of their strong foothold in the global startup ecosystem, and their impressive ability to launch and grow new platforms and services at high speed.\\\"\\u00a0\\r\\n\",\"69\":\"Head of Business Innovation\",\"68\":\"Klavs Hjort\",\"71\":[\"22\"]}}', '2016-10-25 18:03:06', '2016-10-25 18:03:06', 'f3981203-2bce-44a0-b238-a142f072f2fd'),
 ('61', '169', '4', '15', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Study and Recommendations for Making Copenhagen a Nordic FinTech Hub \",\"slug\":\"study-and-recommendations-for-making-copenhagen-a-nordic-fintech-hub\",\"postDate\":1477421992,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":\"\",\"47\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Mapping an Industry Hub\",\"text\":\"In 2015 we were approached by a group of organizations including Finansforbundet, Danish Bankers Association, City of Copenhagen, DJ\\u00d8F, Nets, Saxo Bank, BEC, Tryg and CFIR for an opportunity to analyze and describe FinTech in Copenhagen.\\u00a0\\r\\n\\r\\nThe nine partners wanted to map the Danish FinTech environment, to benchmark Copenhagen against other cities and to identify initiatives that should be taken in order to develop and strengthen the FinTech ecosystem in Copenhagen.\\u00a0\",\"image\":[\"167\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"A 360 Degree View of The Industry\",\"text\":\"Oxford Research as well as Rainmaking was chosen as consultants for the analysis. While Oxford Research has a deep knowledge of the Danish FinTech cluster from an institutional level; Rainmaking intimately knows the Danish startup scene and the international FinTech environment through our Startupbootcamp FinTech accelerators. Together we were able to partner to provide a holistic overview of the ecosystem, spanning both startup and corporate activity. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"white\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"We conducted five workshops focusing on different focus areas: research and education, investors, startups, regulation and public authorities, incubators\\/accelerators and corporates. It was important to the to the validity of the results that actors who know the FinTech ecosystem and the challenges for FinTech all have the opportunity to contribute, so, we involved over 250 people across all levels of the ecosystem, from executives to developers.\\u00a0\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"Download the Summary Report Here: Study and Recommendations for Making Copenhagen a Nordic FinTech Hub \",\"image\":[\"168\"]}},\"new5\":{\"type\":\"videoBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"youtubeVideoId\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=QD7STd0ZP88\"}}},\"72\":[\"168\"],\"67\":\"\",\"69\":\"\",\"68\":\"\",\"71\":\"\"}}', '2016-10-25 18:59:52', '2016-10-25 18:59:52', 'ef72703b-f39e-44b0-8b3b-64c13f70ae3b'),
 ('62', '169', '4', '15', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Making Copenhagen a Nordic FinTech Hub \",\"slug\":\"study-and-recommendations-for-making-copenhagen-a-nordic-fintech-hub\",\"postDate\":1477421940,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":\"\",\"47\":{\"170\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Mapping an Industry Hub\",\"text\":\"In 2015 we were approached by a group of organizations including Finansforbundet, Danish Bankers Association, City of Copenhagen, DJ\\u00d8F, Nets, Saxo Bank, BEC, Tryg and CFIR for an opportunity to analyze and describe FinTech in Copenhagen.\\u00a0\\r\\n\\r\\nThe nine partners wanted to map the Danish FinTech environment, to benchmark Copenhagen against other cities and to identify initiatives that should be taken in order to develop and strengthen the FinTech ecosystem in Copenhagen.\\u00a0\",\"image\":[\"167\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"171\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"A 360 Degree View of The Industry\",\"text\":\"Oxford Research as well as Rainmaking was chosen as consultants for the analysis. While Oxford Research has a deep knowledge of the Danish FinTech cluster from an institutional level; Rainmaking intimately knows the Danish startup scene and the international FinTech environment through our Startupbootcamp FinTech accelerators. Together we were able to partner to provide a holistic overview of the ecosystem, spanning both startup and corporate activity. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"172\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"We conducted five workshops focusing on different focus areas: research and education, investors, startups, regulation and public authorities, incubators\\/accelerators and corporates. It was important to the to the validity of the results that actors who know the FinTech ecosystem and the challenges for FinTech all have the opportunity to contribute, so, we involved over 250 people across all levels of the ecosystem, from executives to developers.\\u00a0\",\"backgroundColour\":\"white\"}},\"173\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"Download the Summary Report Here: Study and Recommendations for Making Copenhagen a Nordic FinTech Hub \",\"image\":[\"175\"]}},\"174\":{\"type\":\"videoBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"youtubeVideoId\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=QD7STd0ZP88\"}}},\"72\":[\"175\"],\"67\":\"\",\"69\":\"\",\"68\":\"\",\"71\":\"\"}}', '2016-10-25 19:06:47', '2016-10-25 19:06:47', '1dd606d0-a6e1-4b51-af3a-fdf4eb52d3c9'),
 ('63', '169', '4', '15', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Making Copenhagen a Nordic FinTech Hub \",\"slug\":\"study-and-recommendations-for-making-copenhagen-a-nordic-fintech-hub\",\"postDate\":1477421940,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":\"\",\"47\":{\"170\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Mapping an Industry Hub\",\"text\":\"In 2015 we were approached by a group of organizations including Finansforbundet, Danish Bankers Association, City of Copenhagen, DJ\\u00d8F, Nets, Saxo Bank, BEC, Tryg and CFIR for an opportunity to analyze and describe FinTech in Copenhagen.\\u00a0\\r\\n\\r\\nThe nine partners wanted to map the Danish FinTech environment, to benchmark Copenhagen against other cities and to identify initiatives that should be taken in order to develop and strengthen the FinTech ecosystem in Copenhagen.\\u00a0\",\"image\":[\"167\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"171\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"A 360 Degree View of The Industry\",\"text\":\"Oxford Research as well as Rainmaking was chosen as consultants for the analysis. While Oxford Research has a deep knowledge of the Danish FinTech cluster from an institutional level; Rainmaking intimately knows the Danish startup scene and the international FinTech environment through our Startupbootcamp FinTech accelerators. Together we were able to partner to provide a holistic overview of the ecosystem, spanning both startup and corporate activity. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"172\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"We conducted five workshops focusing on different focus areas: research and education, investors, startups, regulation and public authorities, incubators\\/accelerators and corporates. It was important to the to the validity of the results that actors who know the FinTech ecosystem and the challenges for FinTech all have the opportunity to contribute, so, we involved over 250 people across all levels of the ecosystem, from executives to developers.\\u00a0\",\"backgroundColour\":\"white\"}},\"173\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"Download the Summary Report Here: Study and Recommendations for Making Copenhagen a Nordic FinTech Hub \",\"image\":[\"175\"]}},\"174\":{\"type\":\"videoBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"youtubeVideoId\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=QD7STd0ZP88\"}}},\"72\":[\"175\"],\"67\":\"\",\"69\":\"\",\"68\":\"\",\"71\":\"\"}}', '2016-10-25 19:06:55', '2016-10-25 19:06:55', '9d761817-a82a-4ad0-8518-5c4dcde84aba'),
 ('64', '108', '4', '15', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"From Idea to Business: Employee Powered Innovation at Majid Al Futtaim\",\"slug\":\"from-idea-to-business-employee-powered-innovation-at-majid-al-futtaim\",\"postDate\":1477406580,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"106\"],\"47\":{\"109\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"A three day hackathon involving over 1300 employees followed by an intensive five day program, transforming hackathon ideas into viable businesses.\",\"image\":[\"100\"]}},\"110\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"Majid Al Futtaim runs Malls and Carrefour hypermarkets across the Middle East, North Africa and Central Asia including the Mall of the Emirates, famous for its indoor ski slope. \\r\\n \\r\\nTheir large physical footprint has given them a distinctive advantage in the retail market, however, with consumer behaviors evolving towards an increasingly digital experience, Majid Al Futtaim wanted to explore how they could be more innovative; both in their customer experiences, and their ways of working.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"111\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"48 hours to create a new experience for Dubai\",\"text\":\"As the first phase of the \\u201cNext Great Moment\\u201d challenge, we created a hackathon to inspire Majid Al Futtaim\\u2019s employees to refine internal ideas for new and innovative products and services in just 48 hours. \\r\\n\\r\\nIn addition to generating new and innovative ideas, the event was designed to give a high volume of employees, from different areas of the business, the experience of applying a more entrepreneurial mindset. It also served to create both internal and external excitement around Majid Al Futtaim\'s innovative approach. \",\"image\":[\"101\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"112\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"From over 1300 applications, 83 talented individuals were selected to attend this intensive experience. By bringing together employees from across the company, we reinforced the importance of collaboration to drive innovation, and a venue to escape the natural silos of the organization. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"113\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"Each attendee had just 60 seconds to pitch their idea, before teams formed around the 10 most popular concepts.\\r\\n\\r\\nThey then had just two days to advance their idea, testing and evolving it through customer interviews, and industry research, before distilling it into a 3 minute pitch to present on the final day.\\r\\n\\r\\nThroughout the weekend, teams were exposed to new methodologies, through an intensive series of exercises and workshops which encouraged attendees to \\u201cThink Big\\u201d, introducing them to Global Trends to further inspire their efforts.\\r\\n\",\"image\":[\"102\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"114\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"From over 1300 applications, 83 talented individuals were selected to attend this intensive experience.\\\"\",\"image\":[\"100\"]}},\"115\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Making the most of every minute\",\"text\":\"We held networking events and icebreakers to encourage teams to utilize the event to meet as many colleagues and industry experts as possible.\\r\\n\\r\\nExpert pitch trainers taught the teams to present with impact, polishing their pitches, and honing presentation skills.\\r\\n\\r\\nMeanwhile, serial entrepreneurs and thought leaders were on hand to offer the teams mentoring and further training, inspiring participants with startup approaches to propel them forward.\",\"image\":[\"103\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"116\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Ideas to move you: From Dubai to London\",\"text\":\"In this supportive, yet challenging, environment, ideas evolved rapidly. \\r\\nA wide range of concepts were developed throughout this process; offering MAF a choice of radically innovative solutions, alongside those which could be quickly implemented to build towards disruption more gradually.\\r\\n\\r\\nTwo of the most exciting ideas won the prize of 5 weeks in London, participating in an immersive Pop-Up Lab which pushed their business models, teamwork and delivery even further.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"117\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"Two of the most exciting ideas won the prize of 5 weeks in London, participating in an immersive Pop-Up Lab which pushed their business models, teamwork and delivery even further.\",\"image\":[\"104\"]}},\"new1\":{\"type\":\"videoBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"youtubeVideoId\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=yEzjhZOcJAg\"}},\"118\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"These teams left the Pop-Up Lab with a new appreciation of Lean Startup approaches, experience conducting customer interviews, and greater insight into working collaboratively in a newly formed team, transcending the silos that typically form in a big business.\",\"image\":[\"105\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"119\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=YXwuN9Ua1AM\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}}},\"72\":[\"100\"],\"67\":\"\\\"The Innovation Challenge provides a unique opportunity for us to foster a culture of innovation amongst our people.\\\"\",\"69\":\"Chief Executive Officer\",\"68\":\"Galal Ismail\",\"71\":[\"107\"]}}', '2016-10-25 19:10:09', '2016-10-25 19:10:09', '9e138849-286a-4f4e-839e-7d3e943dc3d5'),
 ('65', '24', '4', '1', 'en_us', '9', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"How Danske Bank Entered the Startup World\",\"slug\":\"how-danske-bank-is-making-a-splash-in-the-startup-world\",\"postDate\":1477327740,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"23\"],\"47\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"Today, the Hub is the largest startup recruitment site in Denmark. And, we\\u2019re now applying what we\\u2019ve learned across the Nordics, launching Hubs in Norway and Sweden, opening up opportunities for cross-country applications in markets where Danske Bank is most active.\",\"quoteName\":\"Sumname Sumgui\",\"role\":\"Sum role\",\"image\":[\"22\"]}},\"121\":{\"type\":\"imageBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"images\":[\"54\",\"56\",\"93\",\"102\",\"104\"]}},\"42\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"We partnered with Danske Bank to create TheHub.dk, a platform that aims to relieve the pains of Danish startups and provide a platform for Danske Bank to engage with the startup ecosystem. \",\"image\":[\"37\"]}},\"43\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"A long term perspective on growth and support\",\"text\":\"Danske Bank came to us in the Fall of 2015 with an exciting challenge: to create and run a project that would add value to Danish startups and accelerate the growth of early stage companies.\\u00a0\\r\\n\\r\\nDanske Bank wanted to test new forms of engagement with emerging businesses. By actively participating in the Danish startup ecosystem, they can gain early insights into new technologies and business models that could impact their business in the future.\\r\\n\\r\\nBy supporting startups at an early stage, helping them succeed and grow, the bank would also create a wider stream of potential future customers.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"44\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"After over 100 founder interviews, we found three major pain points faced by Danish startups: \",\"text\":\"1. Recruitment: lack of a nationwide, startup focused job board \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Funding: navigating the overwhelming number of investors and funding options to find the right choice\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Knowledge Sharing: capitalizing on the experience of successful founders to accelerate progress\\r\\n\\r\\nWith these three problems in mind, we created The Hub.\\r\\n\",\"image\":[\"36\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"90\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"An online platform, community and resource center \",\"text\":\"Targeting recruitment first, we built a job board tailored specifically to startups. \\r\\n\\r\\nWe found that startups rely on their own networks and traditional job boards for hiring. But they were missing something fit for purpose. Specifically for entrepreneurs, targeting job seekers interested in joining startups.\\r\\n\\r\\nWe\\u2019ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits, converting to 600 weekly applications. This is paired with great feedback from both startups and applicants using the site. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"120\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"We\\u2019ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits, converting to 600 weekly applications.\\\"\",\"image\":[\"39\"]}},\"46\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"We received far more applications through the Hub compared to elsewhere. All the applicants were relevant and part of our target group. For those reasons, I would recommend the Hub (and have already done it)\\\"\",\"quoteName\":\"Happy Hub User\",\"role\":\"\",\"image\":[\"39\"]}},\"47\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"To help navigate the funding options available to Danish startups, our next solution was to create a tool which could match startups with the most relevant options for them, based on their industry, experience, level of maturity and team size. This included profiles of the top 50 investors in Denmark.\",\"image\":[\"35\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"48\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"Knowledge sharing posed the greatest challenge. The majority of the information startups need is topical, specific to their industry, stage and product. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe Hub therefore needed to address the need for both startup specific, and generic content. To achieve this, we\\u2019ve started to develop a mentor matching scheme to pair startups with relevant advisors. \\r\\n\\r\\nMeanwhile, we\\u2019ve also developed a number of tools to share best practices around some of the steps almost all startups follow.  From raising funds to gaining the very first customers.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"49\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Widening The Hub\\u2019s Reach\",\"text\":\"Today, the Hub is the largest startup recruitment site in Denmark. And, we\\u2019re now applying what we\\u2019ve learned across the Nordics, launching Hubs in Norway and Sweden, opening up opportunities for cross-country applications in markets where Danske Bank is most active.\",\"image\":[\"41\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"166\":{\"type\":\"videoBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"youtubeVideoId\":\"c9Y0Zlm1Puc\"}}},\"72\":[\"35\"],\"67\":\"\\u201cWe have partnered with Rainmaking because of their strong foothold in the global startup ecosystem, and their impressive ability to launch and grow new platforms and services at high speed.\\\"\\u00a0\\r\\n\",\"69\":\"Head of Business Innovation\",\"68\":\"Klavs Hjort\",\"71\":[\"22\"]}}', '2016-10-25 21:52:46', '2016-10-25 21:52:46', '0fb3ef76-c325-4097-b94b-c98d0868ef04'),
