lution was to create a tool which could match startups with the most relevant options for them, based on their industry, experience, level of maturity and team size. This included profiles of the top 50 investors in Denmark.\",\"image\":[\"35\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"48\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"Knowledge sharing posed the greatest challenge. The majority of the information startups need is topical, specific to their industry, stage and product. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe Hub therefore needed to address the need for both startup specific, and generic content. To achieve this, we\\u2019ve started to develop a mentor matching scheme to pair startups with relevant advisors. \\r\\n\\r\\nMeanwhile, we\\u2019ve also developed a number of tools to share best practices around some of the steps almost all startups follow.  From raising funds to gaining the very first customers.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"49\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Widening The Hub\\u2019s Reach\",\"text\":\"Today, the Hub is the largest startup recruitment site in Denmark. And, we\\u2019re now applying what we\\u2019ve learned across the Nordics, launching Hubs in Norway and Sweden, opening up opportunities for cross-country applications in markets where Danske Bank is most active.\",\"image\":[\"41\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"166\":{\"type\":\"videoBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"youtubeVideoId\":\"c9Y0Zlm1Puc\"}}},\"72\":[\"35\"],\"67\":\"\\u201cWe have partnered with Rainmaking because of their strong foothold in the global startup ecosystem, and their impressive ability to launch and grow new platforms and services at high speed.\\\"\\u00a0\\r\\n\",\"69\":\"Head of Business Innovation\",\"68\":\"Klavs Hjort\",\"71\":[\"22\"]}}', '2016-10-25 22:05:43', '2016-10-25 22:05:43', 'a18a7724-7fbf-4ebb-aa00-7891ab9e89cd'),
 ('67', '184', '5', '15', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Bitcoin and Blockchain Investing: Interview with Meltem Demirors of DCG\",\"slug\":\"bitcoin-and-blockchain-investing-interview-with-meltem-demirors-of-dcg\",\"postDate\":1477477150,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"16\":[\"15\"],\"18\":[\"183\"],\"17\":[\"longForm\"],\"19\":\"\",\"15\":\"<p>Meltem Demirors, director of community at New York-based&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/dcg.co\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Digital Currency Group (DCG)<\\/a>&nbsp;sits down with Startupbootcamp FinTech MD Jesse Podell to discuss the impact of blockchain, the changing nature of venture capital and the reasons she comes to work every morning.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Jesse:&nbsp;&nbsp;Where do you see DCG\\u2019s fit in the bitcoin and blockchain ecosystem? Are you the 800 pound gorilla?\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Meltem:&nbsp;We talked about this a lot when I first joined DCG \\u2013 Why do we come to work in the morning? What inspires us? What motivates us?\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>I think all of us fundamentally see bitcoin blockchain technology changing the financial system and the broader technology landscape.\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>It doesn\\u2019t matter if we\\u2019re the 800 pound gorilla or the small upstart. I think for us we want to have an outsize impact and be an advocate, an evangelist, and the connector that helps make this industry more successful.\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Jesse:&nbsp;&nbsp;Do you see accelerators as a good idea for bitcoin and blockchain startups?\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Meltem:&nbsp;&nbsp;Yes, absolutely.\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>One thing I have noticed is that people who have gone through an accelerator program were much better at pitching, were much better at selling the value proposition, and were much better at creating a narrative. That skill set cannot be underestimated. You\\u2019re going through this rigorous program that\\u2019s designed to teach you all of these fantastic skills and competencies, and you\\u2019re learning from some of the best corporate VCs, the best corporate strategists, the best VCs, the best startup mentors that you normally wouldn\\u2019t have access to in your network. It\\u2019s a great way to compress that learning in a really short timeline and to really grow your network and also get great PR. No brainer for me.\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Obviously, we\\u2019re super excited to have Startupbootcamp FinTech here and really excited about the startups that will go through your program.\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Jesse: &nbsp;What\\u2019s your general advice for startups who might be applying for an accelerator?\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Meltem:&nbsp;I think people are always a little hesitant about applying. They think: \\u201cOh, it\\u2019s three months away from product development. That\\u2019s difficult. I want to focus on the tech.\\u201d No, no, no, no! Spend three months really getting good at sales, at communicating, at branding, at messaging, building relationships. That is going to do so much more for you than building a great product because growth takes two things. It takes a great product, but it also takes a great sales strategy. Remember that there\\u2019s more to the equation than just the technology and really focus on this opportunity to develop relationships and competencies that are going to help you grow beyond the seed stage.\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Jesse:&nbsp;&nbsp;Where do you see the venture capital model heading in five years?\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Meltem:&nbsp;I think a lot more people are excited about venture capital. A lot of people want to be investors. It\\u2019s like a sexy thing to do right now, which is great. I love it. The more money that goes into the ecosystem, the more ideas start getting thrown around.\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>What I think you\\u2019re seeing, though, is a decoupling of the size of the check that an investor\\u2019s able to write and the value that they\\u2019re able to add to an early stage company. We at DCG invest at the seed stage. We aim for 2% to 5% ownership, but we write smaller checks.\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>What you\\u2019re going to start to see are two different types of investors. You\\u2019re going to see one investor who\\u2019s really focused on network effects, on connectivity, who\\u2019s really focused on value-added services, and another investor that\\u2019s really focused on late stage growth. They\\u2019re going to play two very different roles within the life cycle of a startup.\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Jesse:&nbsp;&nbsp;What advice would you have for companies who want to pitch DCG?\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Meltem:&nbsp; For us, we\\u2019re seed stage investors. What our investing team looks at are three things. Number one, the team. Who are you? What\\u2019s your track record and what\\u2019s your story? Why are you starting this company? We need to see that you have grit and that you have determination and that you really care.\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The second is product. Technically, what have you built? Open source software is notoriously competitive, so having teams that are technically competent is very important.\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Then the last one is market. How do you think about monetization, and what\\u2019s the timeline on that? We\\u2019re different from most VCs in that we\\u2019re not a fund. We don\\u2019t have a certain timeline. If it\\u2019s going to take you 10 years to reach profitability, I think we\\u2019re okay with that, but you need to have a plan and then you need to have a backup plan and a backup plan to the backup plan.\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Jesse:&nbsp;&nbsp;What about the role of Community Manager, how do you see it evolving?\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Meltem:&nbsp;&nbsp;When I started my role was pretty specific. It was focused on developing better connective tissue between our companies. Now that we have a number of strategic investors on board we started to realize the value of having a broad network. For me, it\\u2019s about building the DCG brand, building relationships, and also creating new opportunities and new ways of thinking around how to internalize innovation within a large organization. &nbsp;It\\u2019s about taking the community role, untangling into the various components that really move the needle and making it more of a discipline.\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>To read the full interview, please click<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.linkedin.com\\/pulse\\/my-interview-meltem-demirors-dcg-jesse-podell?published=t\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">&nbsp;here<\\/a>:\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Follow&nbsp;Meltem Demirors on <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/Melt_Dem\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Twitter<\\/a>\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;\\u2013\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/dcg.co\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Digital Currency Group&nbsp;<\\/a>manages a large early stage investment portfolio in the digital currency and blockchain space. Recently they announced venture round with a number of leading financial institutions and venture capital firms including MasterCard, Bain Capital Ventures, New York Life and RRE Ventures. &nbsp;The firm had already established itself as a predominant investor of early stage bitcoin startups, with over 50 holdings currently in its portfolio.\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\"}}', '2016-10-26 10:19:11', '2016-10-26 10:19:11', '8df77bdc-7b35-4841-8d22-f31d8e083e52'),
 ('68', '195', '4', '15', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"How Lloyd\'s Banking Group Stays Ahead of FinTech Evolution\",\"slug\":\"how-lloyds-banking-group-stays-ahead-of-fintech-evolution\",\"postDate\":1477478630,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"178\"],\"47\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Partnering With Market Leaders\",\"text\":\"Since 2014 we have been helping to shape the global evolution of FinTech. Together with market leaders like MasterCard, Lloyds Banking Group, Santander, Thomson Reuters, PWC and Rabobank we are running Startupbootcamp accelerator programs for startups and designing corporate innovation programs, establishing commercial connections between startups and established players.\",\"image\":[\"180\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Global Change With Top Startups\",\"text\":\"Each year we scout upwards of 1400 FinTech startups from across the globe. With accelerator programs in Singapore, London and New York, and 50+ FinTech events across almost every continent. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"Each year we scout upwards of 1400 FinTech startups from across the globe\\\"\",\"image\":[\"179\"]}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Early Access to Innovation\",\"text\":\"We select less than 1% of these startups for a Startupbootcamp cohort. This ensures our partners are collaborating with the best talent, often generating pilots, commercial partnerships and co-created solutions. Meanwhile, through the selection process itself, partners are exposed to evolving technology and business model trends at an early stage.  \",\"image\":[\"181\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"new5\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Staying in Front of the Curve with Lloyd\'s \",\"text\":\"Lloyds Banking Group has been a partner on our Startupbootcamp FinTech program since 2014. The partnership came at a time when the bank was undertaking a large-scale digital transformation program, and presented an ideal platform to test new ideas and connect with the wider FinTech ecosystem. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"new6\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"Lloyds\\u2019 goal is to scan the market for innovation and find new opportunities to provide better service to their customers. The relationship is beneficial for both parties: the FinTech startup has access to subject matter experts, launching customers and scarce assets like data sets. For Lloyds it is beneficial because they are able to learn about new technology, business models, see the results within the market and deduce important lessons to stay ahead and deliver value to their customers. \",\"image\":[\"182\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"new10\":{\"type\":\"quoteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"The relationship with Startupbootcamp has been the first step towards collaborating with startups and to support our digital transformation agenda. By working with innovative partners we are able to deliver even better customer propositions and services.\",\"quoteName\":\"Claire Calmejane\",\"role\":\"Head of Innovation\",\"image\":[\"189\"]}},\"new7\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"Keen to partner with Statupbootcamp\\u2019s portofolio companies, Lloyds has worked with alumni WoraPay \\u2013 a collaboration which is said to have saved Lloyds Banking Group employees 10,000 days of work. \",\"image\":[\"185\"]}},\"new8\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"New Ways of Working\",\"text\":\"For Lloyds, collaborating with the FinTech sector also provides inspiring examples of agility and working practices that refresh Lloyd\\u2019s thinking and approach to delivering digital services. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe partnership gave Lloyds the chance to be involved in dedicated events such as FinTech Lounges and hackathons, presenting another opportunity to experience new ways of working.\\r\\n\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"new9\":{\"type\":\"imageBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"images\":[\"191\",\"193\",\"194\"]}}},\"80\":\"\",\"72\":[\"179\"],\"67\":\"\\u201cOur relationship with Rainmaking has given hundreds of our employees access to new tools and skillsets that they have used to become inspiring intrepreneurs inside Lloyds Banking Group.\\u201d \\r\\n\",\"69\":\"Head of Innovation\",\"68\":\"Claire Calmejane\",\"71\":[\"189\"]}}', '2016-10-26 10:43:50', '2016-10-26 10:43:50', 'd05a1975-6ada-4512-a40f-afee77c637b8'),
 ('69', '211', '5', '15', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"How Do You Define Innovation?\",\"slug\":\"how-do-you-define-innovation\",\"postDate\":1477485203,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"16\":[\"15\"],\"18\":[\"210\"],\"17\":[\"longForm\"],\"19\":\"\",\"15\":\"<p>Innovation is a bit of a messy word. We might feel that we intrinsically grasp its meaning, but how many of us can actually articulate what it means, especially as it relates to our specific business? \\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Innovation has increasingly become a marketing buzzword, diluted by firms selling out of the box solutions to capitalize on what has become a blossoming hype curve.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We wanted to know how to better support our partners in the future and avoid falling into the tropes of others. So, we conducted a survey of over 80 participants from the Rainmaking community that self-identified as working in the corporate innovation management space. The results are illuminating, and worth sharing. &nbsp;<\\/p><p><b>Here<\\/b><b>\\u2019<\\/b><b>s a sample of what the community said about <\\/b><b>\\u201c<\\/b><b>innovation<\\/b><b>\\u201d<\\/b><\\/p><p><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/s3.amazonaws.com\\/rainmaking\\/websiteImages\\/Picture11.png#asset:207\\\"><br><\\/p><p>It is easy to see how the word <i>innovation<\\/i> has become confused and abused. Responses ranged from bringing about sweeping visionary change all the way to solving a specific problem. There\\u2019s a lack of agreement on what the output of innovation should look like.&nbsp;\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>At first glance, the responses can seem at odds. We think this is actually to be expected. Closer inspection shows there are consistent themes:<\\/p><ol><li>There must be a positive change; something done, something created<\\/li><li>That change must be new; sometimes iterative, sometimes radical<\\/li><\\/ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Outcomes for innovation initiatives are defined based on their context in the specific market, industry or organization. It\\u2019s very specific to your circumstances. In summary, the most important definition of innovation is your own. <i>Innovation is<\\/i><i>&hellip;<\\/i><i>in the eye of the beholder.<\\/i>\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><b>Here<\\/b><b>\\u2019<\\/b><b>s the current feeling about the <\\/b><b>\\u201c<\\/b><b>innovation industry<\\/b><b>\\u201d&nbsp;<\\/b>\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p><p><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/s3.amazonaws.com\\/rainmaking\\/websiteImages\\/Picture12.png#asset:209\\\"><br><\\/p><p>We loved the honesty!<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The industry that supports your initiatives can be noisy and fragmented. You\\u2019re fighting to deliver against short and long term objectives. Battling for attention with your core business. What you want is someone that is pragmatic in understanding your specific realities, not traditional strategies from self-proclaimed miracle workers.\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>From the feedback we received,&nbsp;this quote really spoke to us:<\\/p><blockquote>We agree. When you combine this with the breadth of responses on why innovation is important\\u200a&mdash;\\u200afrom keeping the lights on, to delivering something tangible, to improving the world\\u200a&mdash;\\u200ait is clear that there can be a gap in getting from where you are today to where you\\u2019d like to be. The bridge that translates strategy into execution, talk into action.<\\/blockquote>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><b>Start with the biggest risk<\\/b>\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p><p><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/s3.amazonaws.com\\/rainmaking\\/websiteImages\\/Screen-Shot-2016-10-26-at-11.32.37.png#asset:190\\\"><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><img src=\\\"file:\\/\\/localhost\\/Users\\/HattieWillis\\/Library\\/Group%20Containers\\/UBF8T346G9.Office\\/msoclip1\\/01\\/clip_image008.gif\\\" v:shapes=\\\"Picture_x0020_4\\\">There are overlaps with these responses yet the top challenges are clear. Shifting mindsets, placing focus on change, and cultural adoption are the most glaringly consistent roadblocks in large organizations.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><b>While we create resources to support you with more thoughts, insights, tools and frameworks to overcome these challenges, here are a few interesting reads that will be helpful<\\/b>:\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/firstround.com\\/review\\/unlocking-the-benefits-of-self-management-without-going-all-in-on-holacracy\\/\\\">Unlocking the Benefits of Self-Management Without Going All In on Holacracy<\\/a>\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/medium.com\\/swlh\\/the-culture-deck-c4126ec63b18#.u3se1nxvm\\\">The Culture Deck: how people work is as important as what they do<\\/a>\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/medium.com\\/the-corporate-startup\\/five-principles-for-building-corporate-innovation-ecosystems-3b421b7d70e5#.dmjl3qcag\\\">Five Principles for Building Corporate Innovation Ecosystems<\\/a>&nbsp;\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/blog.strategyzer.com\\/posts\\/2016\\/6\\/20\\/why-companies-fail-how-to-prevent-it\\\">Why Companies Fail & How To Prevent It<\\/a>&nbsp;\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/firstround.com\\/review\\/summer-book-recommendations-from-the-smartest-people-we-know\\/\\\">We also loved this curated list of Summer 2016 things to read from the amazing First Round<\\/a>\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A few years old now, yet still relevant today:&nbsp;\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.100open.com\\/top-tips-for-building-an-innovation-culture\\/\\\">Top Tips for Building an Innovation Culture<\\/a>\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=u6XAPnuFjJc\\\">Drive: The surprising truth about what motivates us<\\/a>\\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\"}}', '2016-10-26 12:33:23', '2016-10-26 12:33:23', '800fbb72-2fea-4bae-ba68-26de4842010a'),
 ('70', '24', '4', '15', 'en_us', '11', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"How Danske Bank Engages with Over 500 Startups\",\"slug\":\"how-danske-bank-is-making-a-splash-in-the-startup-world\",\"postDate\":1477327740,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"23\"],\"47\":{\"177\":{\"type\":\"quoteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"Today, the Hub is the largest startup recruitment site in Denmark. And, we\\u2019re now applying what we\\u2019ve learned across the Nordics, launching Hubs in Norway and Sweden, opening up opportunities for cross-country applications in markets where Danske Bank is.\",\"quoteName\":\"Sumname Sumgui\",\"role\":\"Sum role\",\"image\":[\"22\"]}},\"121\":{\"type\":\"imageBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"images\":[\"54\",\"56\",\"93\",\"102\",\"104\"]}},\"42\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"We partnered with Danske Bank to create TheHub.dk, a platform that aims to relieve the pains of Danish startups and provide a platform for Danske Bank to engage with the startup ecosystem. \",\"image\":[\"37\"]}},\"43\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"A long term perspective on growth and support\",\"text\":\"Danske Bank came to us in the Fall of 2015 with an exciting challenge: to create and run a project that would add value to Danish startups and accelerate the growth of early stage companies.\\u00a0\\r\\n\\r\\nDanske Bank wanted to test new forms of engagement with emerging businesses. By actively participating in the Danish startup ecosystem, they can gain early insights into new technologies and business models that could impact their business in the future.\\r\\n\\r\\nBy supporting startups at an early stage, helping them succeed and grow, the bank would also create a wider stream of potential future customers.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"44\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"After over 100 founder interviews, we found three major pain points faced by Danish startups: \",\"text\":\"1. Recruitment: lack of a nationwide, startup focused job board \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Funding: navigating the overwhelming number of investors and funding options to find the right choice\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Knowledge Sharing: capitalizing on the experience of successful founders to accelerate progress\\r\\n\\r\\nWith these three problems in mind, we created The Hub.\\r\\n\",\"image\":[\"36\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"90\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"An online platform, community and resource center \",\"text\":\"Targeting recruitment first, we built a job board tailored specifically to startups. \\r\\n\\r\\nWe found that startups rely on their own networks and traditional job boards for hiring. But they were missing something fit for purpose. Specifically for entrepreneurs, targeting job seekers interested in joining startups.\\r\\n\\r\\nWe\\u2019ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits, converting to 600 weekly applications. This is paired with great feedback from both startups and applicants using the site. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"120\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"We\\u2019ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits, converting to 600 weekly applications.\\\"\",\"image\":[\"39\"]}},\"46\":{\"type\":\"quoteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"We received far more applications through the Hub compared to elsewhere. All the applicants were relevant and part of our target group. For those reasons, I would recommend the Hub (and have already done it)\\\"\",\"quoteName\":\"Happy Hub User\",\"role\":\"\",\"image\":[\"39\"]}},\"47\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"To help navigate the funding options available to Danish startups, our next solution was to create a tool which could match startups with the most relevant options for them, based on their industry, experience, level of maturity and team size. This included profiles of the top 50 investors in Denmark.\",\"image\":[\"35\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"48\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"Knowledge sharing posed the greatest challenge. The majority of the information startups need is topical, specific to their industry, stage and product. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe Hub therefore needed to address the need for both startup specific, and generic content. To achieve this, we\\u2019ve started to develop a mentor matching scheme to pair startups with relevant advisors. \\r\\n\\r\\nMeanwhile, we\\u2019ve also developed a number of tools to share best practices around some of the steps almost all startups follow.  From raising funds to gaining the very first customers.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"49\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Widening The Hub\\u2019s Reach\",\"text\":\"Today, the Hub is the largest startup recruitment site in Denmark. And, we\\u2019re now applying what we\\u2019ve learned across the Nordics, launching Hubs in Norway and Sweden, opening up opportunities for cross-country applications in markets where Danske Bank is most active.\",\"image\":[\"41\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"166\":{\"type\":\"videoBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"youtubeVideoId\":\"c9Y0Zlm1Puc\"}}},\"80\":\"\",\"72\":[\"36\"],\"67\":\"\\u201cWe have partnered with Rainmaking because of their strong foothold in the global startup ecosystem, and their impressive ability to launch and grow new platforms and services at high speed.\\\"\\u00a0\",\"69\":\"Head of Business Innovation\",\"68\":\"Klavs Hjort\",\"71\":[\"22\"]}}', '2016-10-26 12:33:46', '2016-10-26 12:33:46', 'e39e3aa5-65f9-4cf0-9f8b-3378d2104479'),
 ('71', '24', '4', '15', 'en_us', '12', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"How Danske Bank Engages with Over 500 Startups\",\"slug\":\"how-danske-bank-is-making-a-splash-in-the-startup-world\",\"postDate\":1477327740,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"23\"],\"47\":{\"121\":{\"type\":\"imageBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"images\":[\"54\",\"56\",\"93\",\"102\",\"104\"]}},\"42\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"We partnered with Danske Bank to create TheHub.dk, a platform that aims to relieve the pains of Danish startups and provide a platform for Danske Bank to engage with the startup ecosystem. \",\"image\":[\"37\"]}},\"43\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"A long term perspective on growth and support\",\"text\":\"Danske Bank came to us in the Fall of 2015 with an exciting challenge: to create and run a project that would add value to Danish startups and accelerate the growth of early stage companies.\\u00a0\\r\\n\\r\\nDanske Bank wanted to test new forms of engagement with emerging businesses. By actively participating in the Danish startup ecosystem, they can gain early insights into new technologies and business models that could impact their business in the future.\\r\\n\\r\\nBy supporting startups at an early stage, helping them succeed and grow, the bank would also create a wider stream of potential future customers.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"44\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"After over 100 founder interviews, we found three major pain points faced by Danish startups: \",\"text\":\"1. Recruitment: lack of a nationwide, startup focused job board \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Funding: navigating the overwhelming number of investors and funding options to find the right choice\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Knowledge Sharing: capitalizing on the experience of successful founders to accelerate progress\\r\\n\\r\\nWith these three problems in mind, we created The Hub.\\r\\n\",\"image\":[\"36\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"90\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"An online platform, community and resource center \",\"text\":\"Targeting recruitment first, we built a job board tailored specifically to startups. \\r\\n\\r\\nWe found that startups rely on their own networks and traditional job boards for hiring. But they were missing something fit for purpose. Specifically for entrepreneurs, targeting job seekers interested in joining startups.\\r\\n\\r\\nWe\\u2019ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits, converting to 600 weekly applications. This is paired with great feedback from both startups and applicants using the site. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"120\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"We\\u2019ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits, converting to 600 weekly applications.\\\"\",\"image\":[\"39\"]}},\"46\":{\"type\":\"quoteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"We received far more applications through the Hub compared to elsewhere. All the applicants were relevant and part of our target group. For those reasons, I would recommend the Hub (and have already done it)\\\"\",\"quoteName\":\"Happy Hub User\",\"role\":\"\",\"image\":[\"39\"]}},\"47\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"To help navigate the funding options available to Danish startups, our next solution was to create a tool which could match startups with the most relevant options for them, based on their industry, experience, level of maturity and team size. This included profiles of the top 50 investors in Denmark.\",\"image\":[\"35\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"48\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Giving Freely\",\"text\":\"Knowledge sharing posed the greatest challenge. The majority of the information startups need is topical, specific to their industry, stage and product. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe Hub therefore needed to address the need for both startup specific, and generic content. To achieve this, we\\u2019ve started to develop a mentor matching scheme to pair startups with relevant advisors. \\r\\n\\r\\nMeanwhile, we\\u2019ve also developed a number of tools to share best practices around some of the steps almost all startups follow.  From raising funds to gaining the very first customers.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"49\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Widening The Hub\\u2019s Reach\",\"text\":\"Today, the Hub is the largest startup recruitment site in Denmark. And, we\\u2019re now applying what we\\u2019ve learned across the Nordics, launching Hubs in Norway and Sweden, opening up opportunities for cross-country applications in markets where Danske Bank is most active.\",\"image\":[\"41\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"166\":{\"type\":\"videoBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"youtubeVideoId\":\"V3RTOLI33Q0\"}}},\"80\":\"\",\"72\":[\"36\"],\"67\":\"\\u201cWe have partnered with Rainmaking because of their strong foothold in the global startup ecosystem, and their impressive ability to launch and grow new platforms and services at high speed.\\\"\\u00a0\",\"69\":\"Head of Business Innovation\",\"68\":\"Klavs Hjort\",\"71\":[\"22\"]}}', '2016-10-26 12:38:40', '2016-10-26 12:38:40', '07e0e17d-4cb1-489a-9cf8-d54b5e6de94d'),
