 ('74', '57', '4', '15', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Finding the Future of Transportation for Daimler\",\"slug\":\"finding-the-future-of-transportation-for-daimler\",\"postDate\":1477393440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"51\"],\"47\":{\"58\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Finding the Driving Edge of Startup Talent\",\"text\":\"Daimler, a partner of Startupbootcamp Smart Transportation, owner of Mercedes Benz and the largest commercial vehicle manufacturer in the world, came to us looking for startups that could help them gain an edge against competition and stay up to date on emerging technology.  \\r\\n\\r\\nWe helped them source over 1,000 startups from across 18 countries and identified a number of forces that are shaping the future of transportation and mobility.\",\"image\":[\"50\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"59\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Staying In the Fast Lane\",\"text\":\"As cars become connected, electric and autonomous, Daimler recognized that they must identify new innovations early in order to stay at the forefront of current technological advancements. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe challenge was to find the next generation of startups that could help Daimler overtake their competition. \\r\\n\\r\\nWith this in mind, Daimler challenged us to source startup talent, and identify trends that are driving innovation within the smart mobility space. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"60\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\\u00a1Hola Brazil!\",\"text\":\"The Rainmaking sourcing team thoroughly screened the global startup market and sourced the best startups that matched our search criteria.  \\r\\n\\r\\nEurope and Brazil offered exciting opportunities, forming the geographic focus for this project.\\r\\n\\r\\nResponding to global trends, we saw that Brazil\\u2019s growth had opened up new markets and created untapped opportunities for startups. In particular, urbanization and rapid population growth present problems that startups were actively finding innovative solutions to. This led us to a new hotbed of talent that was generally underrepresented in mainstream sources.\",\"image\":[\"52\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"61\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"Europe and Brazil offered exciting opportunities, forming the geographic focus for this project.\\\"\",\"image\":[\"212\"]}},\"62\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Getting the Whole Picture\",\"text\":\"At the end of the two month sourcing period we had: \\r\\n\\u2022 Sourced companies from 87 separate data sources and 18 countries\\r\\n\\u2022 Reviewed a total of 1759 companies; from startup accelerators to company directors\\r\\n\\u2022 Selected 326 companies for further review, filtering this down to 82\\r\\n\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"63\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"Our internal panel reviewed and assessed these startups, refining the selection to a top 40. These were presented back to Daimler alongside a trend report capturing industry insights, further highlighting opportunities for engagement within the startup world.\\r\\n\\r\\nToday Daimler remains actively involved in the startup ecosystem, as a partner in our Smart Transportation & Energy Startupbootcamp and continues to pursue new innovations. \",\"image\":[\"54\"],\"align\":\"right\"}}},\"80\":\"\",\"72\":[\"56\"],\"67\":\"\\u201cPartnering with Startupbootcamp will accelerate our access to innovation and will plug us into an impressive community of alumni, mentors and investors.\\u201d\",\"69\":\"Senior Manager, Business Innovation\",\"68\":\"Dr. Frank Spennemann\",\"71\":[\"55\"]}}', '2016-10-26 12:59:37', '2016-10-26 12:59:37', 'a5e13952-3096-4515-abd0-273e174bb991'),
 ('75', '69', '4', '15', 'en_us', '4', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Strategically Sourcing Startups to Catapult Castrol\\u2019s Business Forward\",\"slug\":\"strategically-sourcing-startups-to-catapult-castrols-business-forward\",\"postDate\":1477395000,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"64\"],\"47\":{\"74\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Going Beyond Motor Oil\",\"text\":\"In 2012, we were approached by Castrol innoVentures to help increase its deal flow and strengthen its presence and visibility in the global startup community.\\u00a0\\r\\n\\r\\nAt the time, Castrol had just set up its strategic innovation and investment arm in order to bring additional value to its existing business areas, and to take Castrol beyond motor oils and lubricants and into future focused revenue streams.\\r\\n\\r\\nTogether with the team at Castrol innoVentures, we designed a global pitch competition to act as a sourcing and screening program, allowing us to meet and evaluate startups relevant for Castrol to work with. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe program resulted in Castrol making a direct investment in one startup and commercial partnerships with seven others. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"71\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"we were approached by Castrol innoVentures to help increase its deal flow and strengthen its presence and visibility in the global startup community.\\\"\",\"image\":[\"68\"]}},\"72\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"How to Put Castrol On the Global Startup Map\",\"text\":\"In today\\u2019s venture capital environment, startups are not short on sources of investment. There are hundreds of institutional firms, angel investors and CVC\\u2019s.                                                                        We needed a way to put Castrol on startups\\u2019 radar as a valuable partner, both to work with, and to have on their cap table.\\r\\n                                                                                                                                                             The focus was for us to find startups innovating in 4 strategic areas: Smart Mobility, next generation engineering, intelligent operations, and responsible Castrol.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"75\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Building a Startup Friendly Brand\",\"text\":\"We built a brand around the project: the Castrol 20\\/20 Challenge. Reflecting perfect vision and complete accuracy in finding the right startups for Castrol.\\r\\n\\r\\nA selection of startup finalists would receive free flights and accommodation to London or Shanghai in order to pitch their business to Venture Capitalists and Castrol executives. The winning team was to receive 10,000 USD.\\r\\n\\r\\nA brand website was launched, promoting the competition to potential applicants and spreading the word throughout the global startup community. Both the brand and website were fundamental in positioning Castrol as a company ready to make investments and meaningfully engage with startups.\",\"image\":[\"73\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"76\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"With our marketing efforts driving competition applications, and our dedicated team of researchers, we reviewed over 2,000 startups.\\r\\n\\r\\nDrawing on our experience mentoring and selecting startups for our Startupbootcamp programs and our own investments, we created a shortlist of 20 companies based on their applications and 1-1 interviews.\\r\\n\\r\\nTogether with Castrol innoVentures, we conducted further interviews to narrow the selection to just five startups in each of two competition finals in London and Shanghai.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"77\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Preparing startups for collaboration with corporates\",\"text\":\"In both London and Shanghai, we worked with the startups and mentors one day prior to the final events to prepare the teams. We helped them hone their pitches and introduced ways that they could more effectively work with major corporations.  \\r\\n\\r\\nThe following day, the startups pitched and met with over 30 Venture Capitalists, alongside executives from Castrol and other notable corporations like 3M.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe events not only provided immense value to the startups, in terms of connections and networking with experts, but also gave Castrol a platform to engage with the startups early on.\",\"image\":[\"67\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"82\":{\"type\":\"imageBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"images\":[\"79\",\"80\",\"81\"]}},\"78\":{\"type\":\"quoteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"Castrol 2020 Challenge provided impressive and innovative ideas and we work with 7 out of 10 teams from the 2012 program\\\"\",\"quoteName\":\"Roy Williamson\",\"role\":\"Castrol InnoVentures, Managing Director\",\"image\":[\"66\"]}},\"83\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Creating and capitalising on investment opportunities\",\"text\":\"Castrol InnoVentures ultimately invested in Greensteam, a ground breaking technology company specialising in energy saving solutions for commercial vessels.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe events proved to be a success, so we hosted a second edition, this time exclusively in Shanghai.\\r\\n\\r\\nTo this day, Castrol innoVentures remains an active player in the mobility space and has made further investments in a range of startups.\\r\\n\",\"image\":[\"65\"],\"align\":\"left\"}}},\"80\":\"\",\"72\":[\"65\"],\"67\":\"\\\"The Castrol 20\\/20 Challenge provided impressive and innovative ideas leading to us working with 7 out of 10 startups from the program\\\"\",\"69\":\"Managing Director, Castrol InnoVentures\",\"68\":\"Roy Williamson\",\"71\":[\"66\"]}}', '2016-10-26 13:06:06', '2016-10-26 13:06:06', 'cd822343-5e63-46f7-adb4-359acca592fd'),
 ('76', '69', '4', '15', 'en_us', '5', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Sourcing Startups to Catapult Castrol\\u2019s Business Forward\",\"slug\":\"strategically-sourcing-startups-to-catapult-castrols-business-forward\",\"postDate\":1477395000,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"64\"],\"47\":{\"74\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Going Beyond Motor Oil\",\"text\":\"In 2012, we were approached by Castrol innoVentures to help increase its deal flow and strengthen its presence and visibility in the global startup community.\\u00a0\\r\\n\\r\\nAt the time, Castrol had just set up its strategic innovation and investment arm in order to bring additional value to its existing business areas, and to take Castrol beyond motor oils and lubricants and into future focused revenue streams.\\r\\n\\r\\nTogether with the team at Castrol innoVentures, we designed a global pitch competition to act as a sourcing and screening program, allowing us to meet and evaluate startups relevant for Castrol to work with. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe program resulted in Castrol making a direct investment in one startup and commercial partnerships with seven others. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"71\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"we were approached by Castrol innoVentures to help increase its deal flow and strengthen its presence and visibility in the global startup community.\\\"\",\"image\":[\"68\"]}},\"72\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"How to Put Castrol On the Global Startup Map\",\"text\":\"In today\\u2019s venture capital environment, startups are not short on sources of investment. There are hundreds of institutional firms, angel investors and CVC\\u2019s. \\r\\n\\r\\nWe needed a way to put Castrol on startups\\u2019 radar as a valuable partner, both to work with, and to have on their cap table. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe focus was for us to find startups innovating in 4 strategic areas: Smart Mobility, next generation engineering, intelligent operations, and responsible Castrol.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"75\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Building a Startup Friendly Brand\",\"text\":\"We built a brand around the project: the Castrol 20\\/20 Challenge. Reflecting perfect vision and complete accuracy in finding the right startups for Castrol.\\r\\n\\r\\nA selection of startup finalists would receive free flights and accommodation to London or Shanghai in order to pitch their business to Venture Capitalists and Castrol executives. The winning team was to receive 10,000 USD.\\r\\n\\r\\nA brand website was launched, promoting the competition to potential applicants and spreading the word throughout the global startup community. Both the brand and website were fundamental in positioning Castrol as a company ready to make investments and meaningfully engage with startups.\",\"image\":[\"73\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"76\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"With our marketing efforts driving competition applications, and our dedicated team of researchers, we reviewed over 2,000 startups.\\r\\n\\r\\nDrawing on our experience mentoring and selecting startups for our Startupbootcamp programs and our own investments, we created a shortlist of 20 companies based on their applications and 1-1 interviews.\\r\\n\\r\\nTogether with Castrol innoVentures, we conducted further interviews to narrow the selection to just five startups in each of two competition finals in London and Shanghai.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"77\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Preparing startups for collaboration with corporates\",\"text\":\"In both London and Shanghai, we worked with the startups and mentors one day prior to the final events to prepare the teams. We helped them hone their pitches and introduced ways that they could more effectively work with major corporations.  \\r\\n\\r\\nThe following day, the startups pitched and met with over 30 Venture Capitalists, alongside executives from Castrol and other notable corporations like 3M.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe events not only provided immense value to the startups, in terms of connections and networking with experts, but also gave Castrol a platform to engage with the startups early on.\",\"image\":[\"67\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"82\":{\"type\":\"imageBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"images\":[\"79\",\"80\",\"81\"]}},\"78\":{\"type\":\"quoteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"Castrol 2020 Challenge provided impressive and innovative ideas and we work with 7 out of 10 teams from the 2012 program\\\"\",\"quoteName\":\"Roy Williamson\",\"role\":\"Castrol InnoVentures, Managing Director\",\"image\":[\"66\"]}},\"83\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Creating and capitalising on investment opportunities\",\"text\":\"Castrol InnoVentures ultimately invested in Greensteam, a ground breaking technology company specialising in energy saving solutions for commercial vessels.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe events proved to be a success, so we hosted a second edition, this time exclusively in Shanghai.\\r\\n\\r\\nTo this day, Castrol innoVentures remains an active player in the mobility space and has made further investments in a range of startups.\\r\\n\",\"image\":[\"65\"],\"align\":\"left\"}}},\"80\":\"\",\"72\":[\"65\"],\"67\":\"\\\"The Castrol 20\\/20 Challenge provided impressive and innovative ideas leading to us working with 7 out of 10 startups from the program\\\"\",\"69\":\"Managing Director, Castrol InnoVentures\",\"68\":\"Roy Williamson\",\"71\":[\"66\"]}}', '2016-10-26 13:10:54', '2016-10-26 13:10:54', '020c22b2-74c4-4c60-a0cb-86649a8a4517'),
 ('77', '86', '4', '15', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Bolstering Trade and Cooperation Between the EU and GCC\",\"slug\":\"bolstering-trade-investment-and-cooperation-between-the-eu-and-gcc\",\"postDate\":1477400400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":\"\",\"47\":{\"87\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"Following the success of our ecosystem development work in the MENA regions, we were trusted to co-create the 2015 EU-GCC program. A pilot initiative intended to promote trade between the EU and GCC as well as increase cooperation between corporates, SME\\u2019s and startups.\\r\\nWe partnered with The Danish Confederation of Industry, Business Europe, and the Federation of Gulf Cooperation Council Chambers (\\u2018GCC\\u2019) to design and deliver this project, funded by the EU Commission.\\r\\n\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"88\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Optimizing Relations\",\"text\":\"Despite a past characterized by sociopolitical challenges, the GCC and EU are increasingly reliant on each other for trade and investment. The GCC stands as the fifth top trading partner with the EU and accounts for over \\u20ac100 Billion in EU goods exports. While trade is increasing steadily year over year, the majority is based on mineral fuels and industrial products. \",\"image\":[\"84\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"89\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"Our challenge was to promote trade bilaterally in underrepresented areas such as services and technology, while also increasing collaboration in the development of new innovations.\",\"image\":[\"85\"]}},\"95\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Building on Existing Platforms\",\"text\":\"Having already built up a strong local presence in the GCC region and Europe, and proven the success of our workshop format through our Startup MENA Program, we were able to draw on our existing network of engaged corporates and ecosystem players to design a series of premium workshops and match-making events.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"white\"}},\"96\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"Over the course of 2015 we ran 24 events across 10 countries, successfully highlighting disruptive startups from the GCC, training entrepreneurs, matching corporates to startups for commercial partnerships, and promoting the Gulf as a market to EU startups and SMEs.\",\"image\":[\"91\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"97\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"We Designed and Delivered:\",\"text\":\"Intensive workshops in Kuwait City, Doha, Muscat, Dubai, Manama, Jeddah, London, Berlin, Brussels and Rome\\r\\n\\r\\nMatch-making events in London and Dubai\\r\\n\\r\\nAn international pitch challenge which toured Kuwait, Bahrain, UAE, Qatar, Saudi Arabia and Oman\\r\\n\\r\\nAn online opportunity matchmaking portal: EU-GCC Connect\\r\\n\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"98\":{\"type\":\"imageBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"images\":[\"92\",\"93\"]}},\"99\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Continuous Improvement\",\"text\":\"Building on the success of the EU-GCC program in 2015, the initiative will continue to run until 2018.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe data and reports generated by Rainmaking will be used as the bedrock of further efforts to increase trade and investment across various industries.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe Danish Confederation of Industry, Business Europe, and the Federation of Gulf Cooperation Council Chambers are all driven to to progress further; forging closer links, removing regulatory barriers, and increasing trade.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}}},\"80\":\"\",\"72\":[\"94\"],\"67\":\"\",\"69\":\"\",\"68\":\"\",\"71\":\"\"}}', '2016-10-26 13:16:57', '2016-10-26 13:16:57', '4adf1093-76f6-4679-9841-a331567726f3'),
