ployees and, industry experts. Through showcasing innovation initiatives and solutions, senior management, different business lines, and individuals are engaged with, and exposed to, innovative processes, solutions and mindsets. This is also seen with the Citi Ventures Catalyst program which engages Citi executives to share industry expertise, open conversations, and align strategic interests to help drive the company\\u2019s innovation agenda. \\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Citi runs multiple accelerator programs in order to engage with startups. Their FinTech accelerator was launched in Tel Aviv in 2013 as part of the Citi Innovation Lab TLV, within Citi\\u2019s global network of innovation centers. Since then, Citi have partnered with Plug and Play to further expand their accelerator programs and engage with FinTech startups. \\r\\n\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In addition, Citi\\u2019s venture capital arm has grown their Investment portfolio to 23 active startups. Through aligning their investment focus with the core business\\u2019 needs: Big Data and Analytics, Commerce Payments, Financial Technology, Marketing and Customer Experience, and Security and Enterprise IT, Citi seeks to invest in cutting edge and highly relevant startups to drive innovation.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}}', '2016-10-26 18:17:57', '2016-10-26 18:17:57', '648fc2e2-2c58-4ff6-b66a-0c91fe16722b'),
 ('98', '232', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"The Rainmaking Sessions - Fostering a corporate innovation culture\",\"slug\":\"the-rainmaking-sessions-fostering-a-corporate-innovation-culture\",\"postDate\":1477501440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"25\":\"1 St Katherine\\u2019s Way, London E1W 4UN\",\"1\":\"<p>Large banks and corporations operate in a risk adverse environment, where products are often built in silos by teams with entrenched cultures and procedures. This is often at odds with the fail fast and pivot mindset of the lean startup methodology of developing innovative products and services. How can large corporates create an innovation culture that includes the enterprise? How can management empower the \\u2018Yes, ands..\\u2019 within teams to lead and convince the \\u2018No, buts&hellip;\\u2019 of the benefits of an entrepreneurial innovation culture?<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Fostering an internal innovation culture&nbsp;<\\/em>will be an interactive, think tank style roundtable where you can hear from industry experts to debate and discuss the current state of the industry as well as future trends with your peers.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You will hear from:\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Rachael Jackson, Solutions, Design, Services, RBS\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Alex Farcet, partner at Rainmaking Innovation\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Moderation \\u2013 Liz Lumley\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><\\/ul><\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Please join us at the Rainmaking Loft to be a part of the Summer Season series of thought provoking Rainmaking Sessions looking at innovation and disruptive trends.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>When: 26 May 2016\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Where: The Rainmaking Loft, 1 St Katherine\\u2019s Way, London E1W 4UN\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Agenda:\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>o&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;8:15 - Arrival at loft for coffee\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>o&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;8:30 \\u2013 Buffet style breakfast served\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>o&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;8:45 - Welcome and talks begin\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>o&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;9:15 - Moderated Roundtable starts\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>o&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;10:30 - Breakfast Roundtable ends\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Spaces are limited, so please RSVP by 23 May 2016 with Cilia Li at&nbsp;<a href=\\\"mailto:cilia@startupbootcamp.org\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">cilia@startupbootcamp.org<\\/a>&nbsp;for your chance to be a part of this special event.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Once you reserve your place, please shout about your attendance by sharing \\u2018I will be adding my views and insights to the #RainmakingSessions on&nbsp;<em>Fostering an internal innovation culture<\\/em>&nbsp;on 26 May 2016!\\u2019 on your social media channels.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Rainmaking Sessions \\u2013 the Summer Season.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Rainmaking Sessions are series of monthly, breakfast roundtables to foster debate, discussion and discourse on the nature of innovation in corporates, FinTech, InsurTech, Digital Health and Smart Transportation.<\\/p>\",\"23\":\"https:\\/\\/www.eventbrite.co.uk\\/e\\/the-rainmaking-sessions-fostering-a-corporate-innovation-culture-tickets-25197718053\",\"24\":\"Rainmaking Loft - London\",\"26\":{\"date\":\"11\\/24\\/2016\",\"time\":\"5:00 PM\"}}}', '2016-10-26 20:35:48', '2016-10-26 20:35:48', 'dbe5e29f-ab84-470b-a9bc-04e402a8038a'),
