 ('105', '235', '3', '15', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"The Rainmaking Sessions - What\'s the matter with payments?\",\"slug\":\"the-rainmaking-sessions-whats-the-matter-with-payments\",\"postDate\":1477556997,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"25\":\"1 St. Katherine\'s Way, London, E1W 1UN\",\"1\":\"<p>Startupbootcamp FinTech\\u2019s 2015 Trend Report highlighted a decrease in the volume of quality startups in the payments space. However, around 60% of UK respondents to a PwC Global FinTech survey think consumer banking and payments are going to be the most disrupted sectors over the next five years. Payments used to define what the industry thought of as FinTech disruption. However, new entrants to the market may have underestimated the relative complexity of payments. Will we see a new payments era emerge that is stronger, more mature and, at last, truly disruptive?\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><i>What\\u2019s the matter with payments?<\\/i>&nbsp;will be an interactive, think tank style roundtable where you can hear from industry experts to debate and discuss the current state of the industry as well as future trends with your peers.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You will hear from:\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Jon Prideaux, CEO at Boku\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Richard Jackson, UK Managing Director, WoraPay\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Moderation \\u2013 Liz Lumley\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Please join us at the&nbsp;Rainmaking Loft&nbsp;to be a part of the Summer Season series of thought provoking&nbsp;Rainmaking Sessions&nbsp;looking at innovation and disruptive trends.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When:&nbsp;16 June 2016\\r\\n\\r\\nWhere:&nbsp;The Rainmaking Loft, 1 St Katherine\\u2019s Way, London E1W 1UN\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nAgenda\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>8:15 - Arrival at loft for coffee\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>8:30 \\u2013 Buffet style breakfa