 ('132', '246', '3', '15', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"The Rainmaking Sessions - Disruptive InsurTech: From now to 2030\",\"slug\":\"the-rainmaking-sessions-disruptive-insurtech-from-now-to-2030\",\"postDate\":1477571063,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"25\":\"1 St. Katherine\'s Way, London, E1W 1UN\",\"1\":\"<p>For years FinTech has dominating with news of investments, advancements and innovation. However, the industry on everyone\\u2019s radar for 2016 is insurance. In order to examine these developments, Rainmaking Innovations, in association with Startupbootcamp InsurTech, invite you to an exclusive breakfast roundtable event looking at digital disruption in insurance.<\\/p><p><span><\\/span><i>Disruptive InsurTech: From now to 2030 - What will your path to success be?<\\/i>&nbsp;will be an interactive, think tank style roundtable where you can hear from industry experts to debate and discuss the current state of the industry as well as future trends with your peers.<\\/p><p><span><\\/span>You will hear from:<\\/p><ul><li>Sabine VanderLinden, MD Startupbootcamp InsurTech<\\/li><li>Carolina Vicente,&nbsp;Director of Digital Marketing, Google<\\/li><li>Moderated by: Liz Lumley, Rainmaking Innovation<\\/li><\\/ul><p>Please join us at the Rainmaking Loft to be a part of the first of a series of thought provoking Rainmaking Sessions looking at innovation and disruptive trends.<\\/p><ul><li>When:&nbsp;28 October 2016<\\/li><li>Where:&nbsp;The Rainmaking Loft, 1 St Katherine\\u2019s Way, London E1W 4UN<\\/li><li>Agenda:<\\/li><li>9:00 - Arrival at loft for coffee<\\/li><li>9:15 - Buffet style breakfast served<\\/li><li>9:45 - Welcome and talks begin<\\/li><li>10:15 - Moderated Roundtable starts<\\/li><li>11:30 - Breakfast Roundtable ends<\\/li><\\/ul><p><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">Spac<\\/span><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">es are limited, so please RSVP&nbsp;for your chance to be a part of this special event.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"23\":\"https:\\/\\/www.eventbrite.co.uk\\/e\\/disruptive-insurtech-from-now-to-2030-registration-26699864012\",\"73\":[\"182\"],\"24\":\"Rainmaking Loft - London\",\"26\":{\"date\":\"10\\/28\\/2016\",\"time\":\"9:00 AM\"}}}', '2016-10-27 12:24:24', '2016-10-27 12:24:24', '6a0b53e1-c47a-4480-8289-cc715cde8c11'),
 ('133', '24', '4', '15', 'en_us', '16', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"How Danske Bank Engages with Over 600 Startups\",\"slug\":\"how-danske-bank-is-making-a-splash-in-the-startup-world\",\"postDate\":1477327740,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"23\"],\"47\":{\"42\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"We partnered with Danske Bank to create TheHub.dk, a platform that aims to relieve the pains of Danish startups and provide a platform for Danske Bank to engage with the startup ecosystem. \",\"image\":[\"37\"]}},\"43\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Participating in the Future \",\"text\":\"Danske Bank came to us in the Fall of 2015 with an exciting challenge: to create and run a project that would add value to Danish startups and accelerate the growth of early stage companies.\\u00a0\\r\\n\\r\\nDanske Bank wanted to test new forms of engagement with emerging businesses. By actively participating in the Danish startup ecosystem, they gain early insights into new technologies and business models that could impact their business in the future.\\r\\n\\r\\nBy supporting startups at an early stage, helping them succeed and grow, Danske Bank also creates a wider stream of potential future customers.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"44\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"After over 100 founder interviews, we found three major pain points faced by Danish startups: \",\"text\":\"1. Recruitment: lack of a nationwide, startup focused job board \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Funding: navigating the overwhelming number of investors and funding options to find the right choice\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Knowledge Sharing: capitalizing on the experience of successful founders to accelerate progress\\r\\n\\r\\nWith these three problems in mind, we created The Hub.\\r\\n\",\"image\":[\"247\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"new1\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"With these three problems in mind, we created The Hub.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"With these three problems in mind, we created The Hub.\",\"image\":\"\"}},\"90\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"An online platform, community and resource center \",\"text\":\"Targeting recruitment first, we built a job board tailored specifically to startups. \\r\\n\\r\\nWe found that startups rely on their own networks and traditional job boards for hiring. But they were missing something fit for purpose. Specifically for entrepreneurs, targeting job seekers interested in joining startups.\\r\\n\\r\\nWe\\u2019ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits, converting to 600 weekly applications. This is paired with great feedback from both startups and applicants using the site. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"120\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"We\\u2019ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits, converting to 600 weekly applications.\\\"\",\"image\":[\"39\"]}},\"46\":{\"type\":\"quoteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"We received far more applications through the Hub compared to elsewhere. All the applicants were relevant and part of our target group. For those reasons, I would recommend the Hub (and have already done it)\\\"\",\"quoteName\":\"Happy Hub User\",\"role\":\"\",\"image\":[\"39\"]}},\"47\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"To help navigate the funding options available to Danish startups, our next solution was to create a tool which could match startups with the most relevant options for them, based on their industry, experience, level of maturity and team size. This included profiles of the top 50 investors in Denmark.\",\"image\":[\"35\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"48\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Giving Freely\",\"text\":\"Knowledge sharing posed the greatest challenge. The majority of the information startups need is topical, specific to their industry, stage and product. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe Hub therefore needed to address the need for both startup specific, and generic content. To achieve this, we\\u2019ve started to develop a mentor matching scheme to pair startups with relevant advisors. \\r\\n\\r\\nMeanwhile, we\\u2019ve also developed a number of tools to share best practices around some of the steps almost all startups follow.  From raising funds to gaining the very first customers.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"49\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Widening The Hub\\u2019s Reach\",\"text\":\"Today, the Hub is the largest startup recruitment site in Denmark. And, we\\u2019re now applying what we\\u2019ve learned across the Nordics, launching Hubs in Norway and Sweden, opening up opportunities for cross-country applications in markets where Danske Bank is most active.\",\"image\":[\"41\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"166\":{\"type\":\"videoBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"youtubeVideoId\":\"V3RTOLI33Q0\"}}},\"80\":\"1\",\"72\":[\"36\"],\"67\":\"\\u201cWe have partnered with Rainmaking because of their strong foothold in the global startup ecosystem, and their impressive ability to launch and grow new platforms and services at high speed.\\\"\\u00a0\",\"69\":\"Head of Business Innovation\",\"68\":\"Klavs Hjort\",\"71\":[\"22\"]}}', '2016-10-27 12:37:47', '2016-10-27 12:37:47', 'ed8c6bb0-39a3-44ba-8a0c-c1d8546a888e'),
 ('134', '24', '4', '15', 'en_us', '17', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"How Danske Bank Engages with Over 600 Startups\",\"slug\":\"how-danske-bank-is-making-a-splash-in-the-startup-world\",\"postDate\":1477327740,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"23\"],\"47\":{\"42\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"We partnered with Danske Bank to create TheHub.dk, a platform that aims to relieve the pains of Danish startups and provide a platform for Danske Bank to engage with the startup ecosystem. \",\"image\":[\"37\"]}},\"43\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Participating in the Future \",\"text\":\"Danske Bank came to us in the Fall of 2015 with an exciting challenge: to create and run a project that would add value to Danish startups and accelerate the growth of early stage companies.\\u00a0\\r\\n\\r\\nDanske Bank wanted to test new forms of engagement with emerging businesses. By actively participating in the Danish startup ecosystem, they gain early insights into new technologies and business models that could impact their business in the future.\\r\\n\\r\\nBy supporting startups at an early stage, helping them succeed and grow, Danske Bank also creates a wider stream of potential future customers.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"44\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"After over 100 founder interviews, we found three major pain points faced by Danish startups: \",\"text\":\"1. Recruitment: lack of a nationwide, startup focused job board \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Funding: navigating the overwhelming number of investors and funding options to find the right choice\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Knowledge Sharing: capitalizing on the experience of successful founders to accelerate progress\\r\\n\\r\\nWith these three problems in mind, we created The Hub.\\r\\n\",\"image\":[\"247\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"249\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"With these three problems in mind, we created The Hub.\",\"image\":\"\"}},\"90\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"An Online Platform, Community and Resource Center \",\"text\":\"Targeting recruitment first, we built a job board tailored specifically to startups. \\r\\n\\r\\nWe found that startups rely on their own networks and traditional job boards for hiring. But they were missing something fit for purpose. Specifically for entrepreneurs, targeting job seekers interested in joining startups.\\r\\n\\r\\nWe\\u2019ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits, converting to 600 weekly applications. This is paired with great feedback from both startups and applicants using the site. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"120\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"               550+ startup profiles          11,000+ weekly visits          600+ weekly applications\",\"image\":[\"39\"]}},\"46\":{\"type\":\"quoteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"We received far more applications through the Hub compared to elsewhere. All the applicants were relevant and part of our target group. For those reasons, I would recommend the Hub (and have already done it)\\\"\",\"quoteName\":\"Happy Hub User\",\"role\":\"\",\"image\":[\"39\"]}},\"47\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"To help navigate the funding options available to Danish startups, our next solution was to create a tool which could match startups with the most relevant options for them, based on their industry, experience, level of maturity and team size. This included profiles of the top 50 investors in Denmark.\",\"image\":[\"35\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"48\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Giving Freely\",\"text\":\"Knowledge sharing posed the greatest challenge. The majority of the information startups need is topical, specific to their industry, stage and product. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe Hub therefore needed to address the need for both startup specific, and generic content. To achieve this, we\\u2019ve started to develop a mentor matching scheme to pair startups with relevant advisors. \\r\\n\\r\\nMeanwhile, we\\u2019ve also developed a number of tools to share best practices around some of the steps almost all startups follow.  From raising funds to gaining the very first customers.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"49\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Widening The Hub\\u2019s Reach\",\"text\":\"Today, the Hub is the largest startup recruitment site in Denmark. And, we\\u2019re now applying what we\\u2019ve learned across the Nordics, launching Hubs in Norway and Sweden, opening up opportunities for cross-country applications in markets where Danske Bank is most active.\",\"image\":[\"41\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"166\":{\"type\":\"videoBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"youtubeVideoId\":\"V3RTOLI33Q0\"}}},\"80\":\"1\",\"72\":[\"36\"],\"67\":\"\\u201cWe have partnered with Rainmaking because of their strong foothold in the global startup ecosystem, and their impressive ability to launch and grow new platforms and services at high speed.\\\"\\u00a0\",\"69\":\"Head of Business Innovation\",\"68\":\"Klavs Hjort\",\"71\":[\"22\"]}}', '2016-10-27 12:44:32', '2016-10-27 12:44:32', 'b4a0be59-0c7f-45da-8159-12a87ce9f6f1'),
