b.\\r\\n\",\"image\":[\"247\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"249\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"With these three problems in mind, we created The Hub.\",\"image\":[\"36\"]}},\"90\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Top Tech Talent\",\"text\":\"Targeting recruitment first, we built a job board tailored specifically to startups. \\r\\n\\r\\nWe found that startups rely on their own networks and traditional job boards for hiring. But they were missing something fit for purpose. Specifically for entrepreneurs. Targeting job seekers interested in joining startups.\\r\\n\\r\\nWe\\u2019ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits, converting to 600 weekly applications. This is paired with great feedback from both startups and applicants using the site. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"120\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"We\\u2019ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits, converting to 600 weekly applications.\",\"image\":[\"39\"]}},\"46\":{\"type\":\"quoteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"We received far more applications through the Hub compared to elsewhere. All the applicants were relevant and part of our target group. For those reasons, I would recommend the Hub (and have already done it)\\\"\",\"quoteName\":\"Happy Hub User\",\"role\":\"\",\"image\":[\"259\"]}},\"47\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Connection With Investors \",\"text\":\"To help navigate the funding options available to Danish startups, our next solution was to create a tool which could match startups with the most relevant options for them, based on their industry, experience, level of maturity and team size. This included profiles of the top 50 investors in Denmark.\",\"image\":[\"39\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"48\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Access to Expert Knowledge\",\"text\":\"Knowledge sharing posed the greatest challenge. The majority of the information startups need is topical, specific to their industry, stage and product. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe Hub therefore needed to address the need for both startup specific, and generic content. To achieve this, we\\u2019ve started to develop a mentor matching scheme to pair startups with relevant advisors. \\r\\n\\r\\nMeanwhile, we\\u2019ve also developed a number of tools to share best practices around some of the steps almost all startups follow.  From raising funds to gaining the very first customers.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"49\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Widening The Hub\\u2019s Reach\",\"text\":\"Today, the Hub is the largest startup recruitment site in Denmark. And, we\\u2019re now applying what we\\u2019ve learned across the Nordics, launching Hubs in Norway and Sweden, opening up opportunities for cross-country applications in markets where Danske Bank is most active.\",\"image\":[\"251\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"166\":{\"type\":\"videoBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"youtubeVideoId\":\"V3RTOLI33Q0\"}}},\"80\":\"1\",\"72\":[\"36\"],\"67\":\"We have partnered with Rainmaking because of their strong foothold in the global startup ecosystem, and their impressive ability to launch and grow new platforms and services at high speed\",\"69\":\"Head of Business Innovation\",\"68\":\"Klavs Hjort\",\"71\":[\"22\"]}}', '2016-10-27 16:02:26', '2016-10-27 16:02:26', '9041556a-5e1f-48db-ba8b-eeb5c8af874d'),
 ('168', '69', '4', '15', 'en_us', '10', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Sourcing Startups to Catapult Castrol\\u2019s Business Forward\",\"slug\":\"strategically-sourcing-startups-to-catapult-castrols-business-forward\",\"postDate\":1477395000,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"64\"],\"47\":{\"74\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Going Beyond Motor Oil\",\"text\":\"In 2012, we were approached by Castrol innoVentures to help increase its deal flow and strengthen its presence and visibility in the global startup community.\\u00a0\\r\\n\\r\\nAt the time, Castrol had just set up its strategic innovation and investment arm in order to bring additional value to its existing business areas, and to take Castrol beyond motor oils and lubricants and into future focused revenue streams.\\r\\n\\r\\nTogether with the team at Castrol innoVentures, we designed a global pitch competition to act as a sourcing and screening program, allowing us to meet and evaluate startups relevant for Castrol to work with. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe program resulted in Castrol making a direct investment in one startup and commercial partnerships with seven others. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"71\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"we were approached by Castrol innoVentures to help increase its deal flow and strengthen its presence and visibility in the global startup community.\\\"\",\"image\":[\"68\"]}},\"72\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"How to Put Castrol On the Global Startup Map\",\"text\":\"In today\\u2019s venture capital environment, startups are not short on sources of investment. There are hundreds of institutional firms, angel investors and CVC\\u2019s. \\r\\n\\r\\nWe needed a way to put Castrol on startups\\u2019 radar as a valuable partner, both to work with, and to have on their cap table. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe focus was for us to find startups innovating in 4 strategic areas: Smart Mobility, next generation engineering, intelligent operations, and responsible Castrol.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"75\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Building a Startup Friendly Brand\",\"text\":\"We built a brand around the project: the Castrol 20\\/20 Challenge. \\r\\n\\r\\nA selection of startup finalists would receive free flights and accommodation to London or Shanghai in order to pitch their business to Venture Capitalists and Castrol executives. The winning team was to receive 10,000 USD.\\r\\n\\r\\nA brand website was launched, promoting the competition to potential applicants and spreading the word throughout the global startup community. Both the brand and website were fundamental in positioning Castrol as a company ready to make investments and meaningfully engage with startups.\",\"image\":[\"73\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"76\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Over 2,000 Startups Reviewed\",\"text\":\"With our marketing efforts driving competition applications, and outreach from our dedicated sourcing team, we attracted and reviewed over 2,000 startups.\\r\\n\\r\\nDrawing on our experience mentoring and selecting startups for our Startupbootcamp programs and our own investments, we created a shortlist of 20 companies based on their applications and 1-1 interviews.\\r\\n\\r\\nTogether with Castrol innoVentures, we conducted further interviews to narrow the selection to just five startups in each of two competition finals in London and Shanghai.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"77\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Preparing Startups for Collaboration with Corporates\",\"text\":\"In both London and Shanghai, we worked with the startups and mentors one day prior to the final events to prepare the teams. We helped them hone their pitches and introduced ways that they could more effectively work with major corporations.  \\r\\n\\r\\nThe following day, the startups pitched and met with over 30 Venture Capitalists, alongside executives from Castrol and other notable corporations like 3M.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe events not only provided immense value to the startups, in terms of connections and networking with experts, but also gave Castrol a platform to engage with the startups early on.\",\"image\":[\"67\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"82\":{\"type\":\"imageBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"images\":[\"79\",\"80\",\"81\"]}},\"78\":{\"type\":\"quoteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"Castrol 2020 Challenge provided impressive and innovative ideas and we work with 7 out of 10 teams from the 2012 program\\\"\",\"quoteName\":\"Roy Williamson\",\"role\":\"Castrol InnoVentures, Managing Director\",\"image\":[\"66\"]}},\"83\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Creating and Capitalising on Investment Opportunities\",\"text\":\"Castrol InnoVentures ultimately invested in Greensteam, a ground breaking technology company specialising in energy saving solutions for commercial vessels.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe events proved to be a success, so we hosted a second edition, this time exclusively in Shanghai.\\r\\n\\r\\nTo this day, Castrol innoVentures remains an active player in the mobility space and has made further investments in a range of startups.\\r\\n\",\"image\":[\"65\"],\"align\":\"left\"}}},\"80\":\"1\",\"72\":[\"65\"],\"67\":\"\\\"The Castrol 20\\/20 Challenge provided impressive and innovative ideas leading to us working with 7 out of 10 startups from the program\\\"\",\"69\":\"Managing Director, Castrol InnoVentures\",\"68\":\"Roy Williamson\",\"71\":[\"260\"]}}', '2016-10-27 16:26:04', '2016-10-27 16:26:04', '29a9f90f-a639-4b06-b1fd-bb803d08b9ce'),
 ('169', '69', '4', '15', 'en_us', '11', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Sourcing Startups to Catapult Castrol\\u2019s Business Forward\",\"slug\":\"strategically-sourcing-startups-to-catapult-castrols-business-forward\",\"postDate\":1477395000,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"64\"],\"47\":{\"74\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Going Beyond Motor Oil\",\"text\":\"In 2012, we were approached by Castrol innoVentures to help increase its deal flow and strengthen its presence and visibility in the global startup community.\\u00a0\\r\\n\\r\\nAt the time, Castrol had just set up its strategic innovation and investment arm in order to bring additional value to its existing business areas, and to take Castrol beyond motor oils and lubricants and into future focused revenue streams.\\r\\n\\r\\nTogether with the team at Castrol innoVentures, we designed a global pitch competition to act as a sourcing and screening program, allowing us to meet and evaluate startups relevant for Castrol to work with. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe program resulted in Castrol making a direct investment in one startup and commercial partnerships with seven others. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"71\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"we were approached by Castrol innoVentures to help increase its deal flow and strengthen its presence and visibility in the global startup community.\\\"\",\"image\":[\"68\"]}},\"72\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"How to Put Castrol On the Global Startup Map\",\"text\":\"In today\\u2019s venture capital environment, startups are not short on sources of investment. There are hundreds of institutional firms, angel investors and CVC\\u2019s. \\r\\n\\r\\nWe needed a way to put Castrol on startups\\u2019 radar as a valuable partner, both to work with, and to have on their cap table. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe focus was for us to find startups innovating in 4 strategic areas: Smart Mobility, next generation engineering, intelligent operations, and responsible Castrol.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"75\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Building a Startup Friendly Brand\",\"text\":\"We built a brand around the project: the Castrol 20\\/20 Challenge. \\r\\n\\r\\nA selection of startup finalists would receive free flights and accommodation to London or Shanghai in order to pitch their business to Venture Capitalists and Castrol executives. The winning team was to receive 10,000 USD.\\r\\n\\r\\nA brand website was launched, promoting the competition to potential applicants and spreading the word throughout the global startup community. Both the brand and website were fundamental in positioning Castrol as a company ready to make investments and meaningfully engage with startups.\",\"image\":[\"73\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"76\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Over 2,000 Startups Reviewed\",\"text\":\"With our marketing efforts driving competition applications, and outreach from our dedicated sourcing team, we attracted and reviewed over 2,000 startups.\\r\\n\\r\\nDrawing on our experience mentoring and selecting startups for our Startupbootcamp programs and our own investments, we created a shortlist of 20 companies based on their applications and 1-1 interviews.\\r\\n\\r\\nTogether with Castrol innoVentures, we conducted further interviews to narrow the selection to just five startups in each of two competition finals in London and Shanghai.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"77\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Preparing Startups for Collaboration with Corporates\",\"text\":\"In both London and Shanghai, we worked with the startups and mentors one day prior to the final events to prepare the teams. We helped them hone their pitches and introduced ways that they could more effectively work with major corporations.  \\r\\n\\r\\nThe following day, the startups pitched and met with over 30 Venture Capitalists, alongside executives from Castrol and other notable corporations like 3M.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe events not only provided immense value to the startups, in terms of connections and networking with experts, but also gave Castrol a platform to engage with the startups early on.\",\"image\":[\"67\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"82\":{\"type\":\"imageBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"images\":[\"79\",\"80\",\"81\"]}},\"78\":{\"type\":\"quoteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"Castrol 2020 Challenge provided impressive and innovative ideas and we work with 7 out of 10 teams from the 2012 program\\\"\",\"quoteName\":\"Roy Williamson\",\"role\":\"Castrol InnoVentures, Managing Director\",\"image\":[\"66\"]}},\"83\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Creating and Capitalising on Investment Opportunities\",\"text\":\"Castrol InnoVentures ultimately invested in Greensteam, a ground breaking technology company specialising in energy saving solutions for commercial vessels.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe events proved to be a success, so we hosted a second edition, this time exclusively in Shanghai.\\r\\n\\r\\nTo this day, Castrol innoVentures remains an active player in the mobility space and has made further investments in a range of startups.\\r\\n\",\"image\":[\"65\"],\"align\":\"left\"}}},\"80\":\"1\",\"72\":[\"65\"],\"67\":\"The Castrol 20\\/20 Challenge provided impressive and innovative ideas leading to us working with 7 out of 10 startups from the program\",\"69\":\"Managing Director, Castrol InnoVentures\",\"68\":\"Roy Williamson\",\"71\":[\"260\"]}}', '2016-10-27 16:26:22', '2016-10-27 16:26:22', '8678a41a-2044-4a59-a8a0-1981bbebd630'),
 ('170', '57', '4', '15', 'en_us', '8', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Finding the Future of Transportation for Daimler\",\"slug\":\"finding-the-future-of-transportation-for-daimler\",\"postDate\":1477393440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"51\"],\"47\":{\"58\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Finding the Driving Edge of Startup Talent\",\"text\":\"Daimler, a partner of Startupbootcamp Smart Transportation, owner of Mercedes Benz and the largest commercial vehicle manufacturer in the world, came to us looking for startups that could help them gain an edge against competition and stay up to date on emerging technology.  \\r\\n\\r\\nWe sourced over 1,000 startups from across 18 countries and identified a number of forces that are shaping the future of transportation and mobility.\",\"image\":[\"50\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"252\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"We sourced over 1,000 startups from across 18 countries and identified a number of forces that are shaping the future of transportation and mobility.\\\"\",\"image\":\"\"}},\"59\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Staying In the Fast Lane\",\"text\":\"As cars have become connected, electric and autonomous, Daimler has recognized that they must identify new innovations early in order to stay at the forefront of current technological advancements. \\r\\n\\r\\nOur challenge was to find the next generation of startups that could help Daimler overtake their competition. \\r\\n\\r\\nWith this in mind, Daimler asked us to source startup talent, and identify trends that are driving innovation within the smart mobility space. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"60\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\\u00a1Hola Brazil!\",\"text\":\"Our sourcing team screened startups from around the globe. And, identified the most interesting startups for Daimler.  \\r\\n\\r\\nBeginning with a world wide scope, we quickly identified Europe and Brazil as exciting areas for new talent.\\r\\n\\r\\nResponding to global trends, we saw that Brazil\\u2019s growth had opened up new markets and created untapped opportunities for startups. In particular, urbanization and rapid population growth present problems that startups are actively finding innovative solutions to. This led us to a new hotbed of talent that was generally underrepresented in mainstream sources.\",\"image\":[\"52\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"61\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"Beginning with a world wide scope, we quickly identified Europe and Brazil as exciting areas for new talent.\\\"\",\"image\":[\"212\"]}},\"62\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Getting the Whole Picture\",\"text\":\"At the end of the two month sourcing period we had: \\r\\n\\r\\n\\u2022 Sourced startups from 87 data sources \\r\\n\\r\\n\\u2022 Covered 18 countries\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u2022 Reviewed 1759 startups\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u2022 Selected 326 startups for further review\\r\\n\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"63\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Delivering Startups, Trends, and Actionable Intel\",\"text\":\"Our internal panel reviewed and assessed these startups, refining the selection to a top 40. These were presented back to Daimler alongside a trend report capturing industry insights, further highlighting opportunities for engagement within the startup world.\\r\\n\\r\\nToday Daimler remains actively involved in the startup ecosystem, as a partner in our Smart Transportation & Energy Startupbootcamp and continues to pursue new innovations. \",\"image\":[\"54\"],\"align\":\"right\"}}},\"80\":\"1\",\"72\":[\"262\"],\"67\":\"\\u201cPartnering with Startupbootcamp will accelerate our access to innovation and will plug us into an impressive community of alumni, mentors and investors.\\u201d\",\"69\":\"Senior Manager, Business Innovation\",\"68\":\"Dr. Frank Spennemann\",\"71\":[\"261\"]}}', '2016-10-27 16:57:23', '2016-10-27 16:57:23', '54fa51ba-4540-4782-83f8-57bbf5810846'),
 ('171', '57', '4', '15', 'en_us', '9', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Finding the Future of Transportation for Daimler\",\"slug\":\"finding-the-future-of-transportation-for-daimler\",\"postDate\":1477393440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"51\"],\"47\":{\"58\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Finding the Driving Edge of Startup Talent\",\"text\":\"Daimler, a partner of Startupbootcamp Smart Transportation, owner of Mercedes Benz and the largest commercial vehicle manufacturer in the world, came to us looking for startups that could help them gain an edge against competition and stay up to date on emerging technology.  \\r\\n\\r\\nWe sourced over 1,000 startups from across 18 countries and identified a number of forces that are shaping the future of transportation and mobility.\",\"image\":[\"50\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"252\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"We sourced over 1,000 startups from across 18 countries and identified a number of forces that are shaping the future of transportation and mobility.\\\"\",\"image\":\"\"}},\"59\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Staying In the Fast Lane\",\"text\":\"As cars have become connected, electric and autonomous, Daimler has recognized that they must identify new innovations early in order to stay at the forefront of current technological advancements. \\r\\n\\r\\nOur challenge was to find the next generation of startups that could help Daimler overtake their competition. \\r\\n\\r\\nWith this in mind, Daimler asked us to source startup talent, and identify trends that are driving innovation within the smart mobility space. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"60\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\\u00a1Hola Brazil!\",\"text\":\"Our sourcing team screened startups from around the globe. And, identified the most interesting startups for Daimler.  \\r\\n\\r\\nBeginning with a world wide scope, we quickly identified Europe and Brazil as exciting areas for new talent.\\r\\n\\r\\nResponding to global trends, we saw that Brazil\\u2019s growth had opened up new markets and created untapped opportunities for startups. In particular, urbanization and rapid population growth present problems that startups are actively finding innovative solutions to. This led us to a new hotbed of talent that was generally underrepresented in mainstream sources.\",\"image\":[\"52\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"61\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"Beginning with a world wide scope, we quickly identified Europe and Brazil as exciting areas for new talent.\\\"\",\"image\":[\"212\"]}},\"62\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Getting the Whole Picture\",\"text\":\"At the end of the two month sourcing period we had: \\r\\n\\r\\n\\u2022 Sourced startups from 87 data sources \\r\\n\\r\\n\\u2022 Covered 18 countries\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u2022 Reviewed 1759 startups\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u2022 Selected 326 startups for further review\\r\\n\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"63\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Delivering Startups, Trends, and Actionable Intel\",\"text\":\"Our internal panel reviewed and assessed these startups, refining the selection to a top 40. These were presented back to Daimler alongside a trend report capturing industry insights, further highlighting opportunities for engagement within the startup world.\\r\\n\\r\\nToday Daimler remains actively involved in the startup ecosystem, as a partner in our Smart Transportation & Energy Startupbootcamp and continues to pursue new innovations. \",\"image\":[\"54\"],\"align\":\"right\"}}},\"80\":\"1\",\"72\":[\"262\"],\"67\":\"\\u201cPartnering with Startupbootcamp will accelerate our access to innovation and will plug us into an impressive community of alumni, mentors and investors.\\u201d\",\"69\":\"Senior Manager, Business Innovation\",\"68\":\"Dr. Frank Spennemann\",\"71\":[\"263\"]}}', '2016-10-27 17:04:48', '2016-10-27 17:04:48', 'e372175e-b385-4908-843f-a0b696727409'),
