 ('225', '211', '5', '15', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"How Do You Define Innovation?\",\"slug\":\"how-do-you-define-innovation\",\"postDate\":1477485180,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"16\":[\"15\"],\"18\":[\"210\"],\"17\":[\"longForm\"],\"19\":\"\",\"15\":\"<p>Innovation is a bit of a messy word. We might feel that we intrinsically grasp its meaning, but how many of us can actually articulate what it means, especially as it relates to our specific business?<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Innovation has increasingly become a marketing buzzword, diluted by firms selling out of the box solutions to capitalize on what has become a blossoming hype curve.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We wanted to know how to better support our partners in the future and avoid falling into the tropes of others. So, we conducted a survey of over 80 participants from the Rainmaking community that self-identified as working in the corporate innovation management space. The results are illuminating, and worth sharing. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Here<\\/strong><strong>\\u2019<\\/strong><strong>s a sample of what the community said about <\\/strong><strong>\\u201c<\\/strong><strong>innovation<\\/strong><strong>\\u201d<\\/strong><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/s3.amazonaws.com\\/rainmaking\\/websiteImages\\/Picture11.png#asset:207:url\\\" alt=\\\"Picture11.png#asset:207\\\">It is easy to see how the word <em>innovation<\\/em> has become confused and abused. Responses ranged from bringing about sweeping visionary change all the way to solving a specific problem. There\\u2019s a lack of agreement on what the output of innovation should look like.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>At first glance, the responses can seem at odds. We think this is actually to be expected. Closer inspection shows there are consistent themes:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol><li>There must be a positive change; something done, something created<\\/li><li>That change must be new; sometimes iterative, sometimes radical<\\/li><\\/ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Outcomes for innovation initiatives are defined based on their context in the specific market, industry or organization. It\\u2019s very specific to your circumstances. In summary, the most important definition of innovation is your own. <em>Innovation is<\\/em><em>&hellip;<\\/em><em>in the eye of the beholder.<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><\\/em><strong>Here<\\/strong><strong>\\u2019<\\/strong><strong>s the current feeling about the <\\/strong><strong>\\u201c<\\/strong><strong>innovation industry<\\/strong><strong>\\u201d&nbsp;<\\/strong><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/s3.amazonaws.com\\/rainmaking\\/websiteImages\\/Picture12.png#asset:209:url\\\" alt=\\\"Picture12.png#asset:209\\\">We loved the honesty!<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The industry that supports your initiatives can be noisy and fragmented. You\\u2019re fighting to deliver against short and long term objectives. Battling for attention with your core business. What you want is someone that is pragmatic in understanding your specific realities, not traditional strategies from self-proclaimed miracle workers.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>From the feedback we received,&nbsp;this quote really spoke to us:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<blockquote>We agree. When you combine this with the breadth of responses on why innovation is important\\u200a&mdash;\\u200afrom keeping the lights on, to delivering something tangible, to improving the world\\u200a&mdash;\\u200ait is clear that there can be a gap in getting from where you are today to where you\\u2019d like to be. The bridge that translates strategy into execution, talk into action.<\\/blockquote>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Start with the biggest risk<img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/s3.amazonaws.com\\/rainmaking\\/websiteImages\\/Screen-Shot-2016-10-26-at-11.32.37.png#asset:190:url\\\" alt=\\\"Screen-Shot-2016-10-26-at-11.32.37.png#a\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(41, 50, 61);\\\"><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>There are overlaps with these responses yet the top challenges are clear. Shifting mindsets, placing focus on change, and cultural adoption are the most glaringly consistent roadblocks in large organizations.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>While we create resources to support you with more thoughts, insights, tools and frameworks to overcome these challenges, here are a few interesting reads that will be helpful<\\/strong>:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/firstround.com\\/review\\/unlocking-the-benefits-of-self-management-without-going-all-in-on-holacracy\\/\\\">Unlocking the Benefits of Self-Management Without Going All In on Holacracy<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/firstround.com\\/review\\/unlocking-the-benefits-of-self-management-without-going-all-in-on-holacracy\\/\\\"><\\/a><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/medium.com\\/swlh\\/the-culture-deck-c4126ec63b18#.u3se1nxvm\\\">The Culture Deck: how people work is as important as what they do<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/medium.com\\/swlh\\/the-culture-deck-c4126ec63b18#.u3se1nxvm\\\"><\\/a><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/medium.com\\/the-corporate-startup\\/five-principles-for-building-corporate-innovation-ecosystems-3b421b7d70e5#.dmjl3qcag\\\">Five Principles for Building Corporate Innovation Ecosystems<\\/a>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/blog.strategyzer.com\\/posts\\/2016\\/6\\/20\\/why-companies-fail-how-to-prevent-it\\\">Why Companies Fail & How To Prevent It<\\/a>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/firstround.com\\/review\\/summer-book-recommendations-from-the-smartest-people-we-know\\/\\\">We also loved this curated list of Summer 2016 things to read from the amazing First Round<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/firstround.com\\/review\\/summer-book-recommendations-from-the-smartest-people-we-know\\/\\\"><\\/a>A few years old now, yet still relevant today:&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.100open.com\\/top-tips-for-building-an-innovation-culture\\/\\\">Top Tips for Building an Innovation Culture<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.100open.com\\/top-tips-for-building-an-innovation-culture\\/\\\"><\\/a><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=u6XAPnuFjJc\\\">Drive: The surprising truth about what motivates us<\\/a><\\/p>\"}}', '2016-10-31 12:33:05', '2016-10-31 12:33:05', 'c330a006-a470-4c82-8097-5f5c159685ea'),
 ('226', '211', '5', '15', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"How Do You Define Innovation?\",\"slug\":\"how-do-you-define-innovation\",\"postDate\":1477485180,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"16\":[\"15\"],\"18\":[\"210\"],\"17\":[\"longForm\"],\"19\":\"\",\"15\":\"<p>Innovation is a bit of a messy word. We might feel that we intrinsically grasp its meaning, but how many of us can actually articulate what it means, especially as it relates to our specific business?<\\/p><p>Innovation has increasingly become a marketing buzzword, diluted by firms selling out of the box solutions to capitalize on what has become a blossoming hype curve.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>We wanted to know how to better support our partners in the future and avoid falling into the tropes of others. So, we conducted a survey of over 80 participants from the Rainmaking community that self-identified as working in the corporate innovation management space. The results are illuminating, and worth sharing. &nbsp;<\\/p><p><strong>Here<\\/strong><strong>\\u2019<\\/strong><strong>s a sample of what the community said about <\\/strong><strong>\\u201c<\\/strong><strong>innovation<\\/strong><strong>\\u201d<\\/strong><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/s3.amazonaws.com\\/rainmaking\\/websiteImages\\/Picture11.png#asset:207:url\\\" alt=\\\"Picture11.png#asset:207\\\">It is easy to see how the word <em>innovation<\\/em> has become confused and abused. Responses ranged from bringing about sweeping visionary change all the way to solving a specific problem. There\\u2019s a lack of agreement on what the output of innovation should look like.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>At first glance, the responses can seem at odds. We think this is actually to be expected. Closer inspection shows there are consistent themes:<\\/p><ol><li>There must be a positive change; something done, something created<\\/li><li>That change must be new; sometimes iterative, sometimes radical<\\/li><li><em><\\/em><\\/li><\\/ol><p>Outcomes for innovation initiatives are defined based on their context in the specific market, industry or organization. It\\u2019s very specific to your circumstances. In summary, the most important definition of innovation is your own. <em>Innovation is<\\/em><em>&hellip;<\\/em><em>in the eye of the beholder.<\\/em><\\/p><p><em><\\/em><strong>Here<\\/strong><strong>\\u2019<\\/strong><strong>s the current feeling about the <\\/strong><strong>\\u201c<\\/strong><strong>innovation industry<\\/strong><strong>\\u201d&nbsp;<\\/strong><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/s3.amazonaws.com\\/rainmaking\\/websiteImages\\/Picture12.png#asset:209:url\\\" alt=\\\"Picture12.png#asset:209\\\">We loved the honesty!<\\/p><p>The industry that supports your initiatives can be noisy and fragmented. You\\u2019re fighting to deliver against short and long term objectives. Battling for attention with your core business. What you want is someone that is pragmatic in understanding your specific realities, not traditional strategies from self-proclaimed miracle workers.<\\/p><p>From the feedback we received,&nbsp;this quote really spoke to us:<\\/p><blockquote>We agree. When you combine this with the breadth of responses on why innovation is important\\u200a&mdash;\\u200afrom keeping the lights on, to delivering something tangible, to improving the world\\u200a&mdash;\\u200ait is clear that there can be a gap in getting from where you are today to where you\\u2019d like to be. The bridge that translates strategy into execution, talk into action.<br><br><\\/blockquote><h2>Start with the biggest risk<img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/s3.amazonaws.com\\/rainmaking\\/websiteImages\\/Screen-Shot-2016-10-26-at-11.32.37.png#asset:190:url\\\" alt=\\\"Screen-Shot-2016-10-26-at-11.32.37.png#a\\\" style=\\\"font-family: Arial, \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(41, 50, 61);\\\"><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>There are overlaps with these responses yet the top challenges are clear. Shifting mindsets, placing focus on change, and cultural adoption are the most glaringly consistent roadblocks in large organizations.<\\/p><p><strong>While we create resources to support you with more thoughts, insights, tools and frameworks to overcome these challenges, here are a few interesting reads that will be helpful<\\/strong>:<\\/p><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/firstround.com\\/review\\/unlocking-the-benefits-of-self-management-without-going-all-in-on-holacracy\\/\\\">Unlocking the Benefits of Self-Management Without Going All In on Holacracy<\\/a><\\/p><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/firstround.com\\/review\\/unlocking-the-benefits-of-self-management-without-going-all-in-on-holacracy\\/\\\"><\\/a><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/medium.com\\/swlh\\/the-culture-deck-c4126ec63b18#.u3se1nxvm\\\">The Culture Deck: how people work is as important as what they do<\\/a><\\/p><p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/medium.com\\/swlh\\/the-culture-deck-c4126ec63b18#.u3se1nxvm\\\"><\\/a><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/medium.com\\/the-corporate-startup\\/five-principles-for-building-corporate-innovation-ecosystems-3b421b7d70e5#.dmjl3qcag\\\">Five Principles for Building Corporate Innovation Ecosystems<\\/a>&nbsp;<\\/p><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/blog.strategyzer.com\\/posts\\/2016\\/6\\/20\\/why-companies-fail-how-to-prevent-it\\\">Why Companies Fail & How To Prevent It<\\/a>&nbsp;<\\/p><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/firstround.com\\/review\\/summer-book-recommendations-from-the-smartest-people-we-know\\/\\\">We also loved this curated list of Summer 2016 things to read from the amazing First Round<\\/a><\\/p><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/firstround.com\\/review\\/summer-book-recommendations-from-the-smartest-people-we-know\\/\\\"><\\/a>A few years old now, yet still relevant today:&nbsp;<\\/p><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.100open.com\\/top-tips-for-building-an-innovation-culture\\/\\\">Top Tips for Building an Innovation Culture<\\/a><\\/p><p><a href=\