 ('264', '142', '5', '15', 'en_us', '7', '', '{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"The Key To Fostering Corporate Innovation Culture? Inside Out!\",\"slug\":\"the-key-to-fostering-corporate-innovation-culture-inside-out\",\"postDate\":1464971460,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"16\":[\"15\"],\"18\":[\"141\"],\"17\":[\"longForm\"],\"19\":\"\",\"15\":\"<h2>How to Foster An Innovation Culture<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Many large firms are currently grappling with ways to incorporate a more innovative culture into their development and organisational environments. As with any large transformational project, success or failure tend to depend on the right mix of culture and human relationships.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>This was the main crux of the discussion at the inaugural Rainmaking Session\\u200a&mdash;\\u200aHow to foster a corporate innovation culture\\u200a&mdash;\\u200ahosted by Rainmaking Innovation in May.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>A wide range of corporate innovation leaders and learners from organisations as diverse as Standard & Poors, BP and SwissRe gathered to hear a discussion led by Rachael Jackson, Solutions, Design, Services at RBS and Alex Farcet, partner at Rainmaking Innovation.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The conversation around the table, conducted under the Chatham House Rule, came thick and fast as participants&nbsp;relayed stories of their own companies\\u2019 internal challenges, strategies and successes. The only interruption to the discussion came when two enormous anti-terrorist transformer helicopters buzzed over&nbsp;the Rainmaking Loft!<\\/p><p><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/s3.amazonaws.com\\/rainmaking\\/websiteImages\\/Picture1_161031_172030.png#asset:309\\\"><br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Our Findings<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The main findings from the roundtable were as follows:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Innovation leaders at corporations need to operate with one leg inside an organisation and one leg outside. Being outside a firm allows the leaders to learn and discover new technologies and new business models that can transform the enterprise. While keeping a foot inside a company, keeps lines of communication and collaboration open with senior people at the firm.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>This line of talk moved onto a debate on whether innovation departments need to be centralised, and separate from the main organisation, with their own staff, budget and authority, or decentralised. The centralised model had the advantages of a separate budget line which would allow projects to develop without relying on the P&L of separate business units. The decentralised approach emphasised the importance of encouraging the entire firm to engage in innovation projects and activities.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Innovation tends to signal change for most companies and change is scary. People and culture are key to ensuring that establishing an&nbsp;innovation culture is seen as beneficial and empowering to the rest of the organisation.<img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/s3.amazonaws.com\\/rainmaking\\/websiteImages\\/1KuyS3TbSOtuUIL3loV17JA.png#asset:140:url\\\" alt=\\\"1KuyS3TbSOtuUIL3loV17JA.png#asset:140\\\"><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Many around the Rainmaking Session breakfast table recognised that a large number of&nbsp;innovation projects were led by either senior management or staff working hands on in development. It was the so-called \\u2018middle layer\\u2019 that was most in need of empowerment when it came to innovation. A large proportion of the group argued that this \\u2018middle layer\\u2019 was not incentivised to try anything new or to embark on innovation projects that have the possibility of failure embedded in their DNA.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Innovation projects are hard to measure, and including metrics at all might be detrimental to its successes. However, most large corporates operate in a risk culture that requires performance metrics and measurement. The \\u2018can\\u2019t live with metrics\\/can\\u2019t live without metrics\\u2019 debate continues.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Advice to Startups<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Finally, the roundtable debate focused engaging with and working with startups. The large corporate around the table all expressed an interest and a desire to work with startups\\u200a&mdash;\\u200agiven that the search for new technologies and solutions is often found in the startup community.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Their advice for any startup looking to sell into or partner with a larger organisation was to make sure that they presented their value proposition in a way that made sense for the corporate and their clients\\u2019 needs. If that value proposition was met correctly, a partnership between a corporate and a startup would be more likely to be successful. These successful projects could then be used as evidence to the rest of the company that embarking on an innovation culture was beneficial and worthwhile.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Please join us, or invite a colleague, for our next Rainmaking Session on June 16th\\u200a&mdash;\\u200aWhat\\u2019s the matter with payments?<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>You will hear from:<\\/em>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li><em>Jon Prideaux, CEO at Boku<\\/em><\\/li><li><em>Richard Jackson, UK Managing Director, WoraPay<\\/em><\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.eventbrite.co.uk\\/e\\/the-rainmaking-sessions-whats-the-matter-with-payments-tickets-25602215917\\\">Learn more here<\\/a><\\/em><\\/p>\"}}', '2016-10-31 18:03:09', '2016-10-31 18:03:09', '69797729-57eb-4a5b-b58c-ceddfd902df4'),
 ('265', '24', '4', '15', 'en_us', '25', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Danske Bank Engages with Over 600 Startups\",\"slug\":\"how-danske-bank-is-making-a-splash-in-the-startup-world\",\"postDate\":1477327740,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"23\"],\"47\":{\"42\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"We partnered with Danske Bank to create TheHub.dk, a platform that aims to relieve the pains of Danish startups and provide a platform for Danske Bank to engage with the startup ecosystem. \",\"image\":[\"37\"]}},\"43\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Participating in the Future \",\"text\":\"Danske Bank came to us in the Fall of 2015 with an exciting challenge: to create and run a project that would add value to Danish startups and accelerate the growth of early stage companies.\\u00a0\\r\\n\\r\\nDanske Bank wanted to test new forms of engagement with emerging businesses. By actively participating in the Danish startup ecosystem, they gain early insights into new technologies and business models that could impact their business in the future.\\r\\n\\r\\nBy supporting startups at an early stage, helping them succeed and grow, Danske Bank also creates a wider stream of potential future customers.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"44\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"An Online Recruiting Platform, Community and Resource Center \",\"text\":\"After over 100 founder interviews, we found three major pain points faced by Danish startups: \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Recruitment: lack of a nationwide, startup focused job board \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Funding: navigating the overwhelming number of investors and funding options to find the right choice\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Knowledge Sharing: capitalizing on the experience of successful founders to accelerate progress\\r\\n\\r\\nWith these three problems in mind, we created The Hub.\\r\\n\",\"image\":[\"247\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"249\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"With these three problems in mind, we created The Hub.\",\"image\":[\"36\"]}},\"90\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Top Tech Talent\",\"text\":\"Targeting recruitment first, we built a job board tailored specifically to startups. \\r\\n\\r\\nWe found that startups rely on their own networks and traditional job boards for hiring. But they were missing something fit for purpose. Specifically for entrepreneurs. Targeting job seekers interested in joining startups.\\r\\n\\r\\nWe\\u2019ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits, converting to 600 weekly applications. This is paired with great feedback from both startups and applicants using the site. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"120\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"We\\u2019ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits, converting to 600 weekly applications.\",\"image\":[\"39\"]}},\"46\":{\"type\":\"quoteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"We received far more applications through the Hub compared to elsewhere. All the applicants were relevant and part of our target group. For those reasons, I would recommend the Hub (and have already done it)\\\"\",\"quoteName\":\"Happy Hub User\",\"role\":\"\",\"image\":[\"259\"]}},\"47\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Connection With Investors \",\"text\":\"To help navigate the funding options available to Danish startups, our next solution was to create a tool which could match startups with the most relevant options for them, based on their industry, experience, level of maturity and team size. This included profiles of the top 50 investors in Denmark.\",\"image\":[\"39\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"48\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Access to Expert Knowledge\",\"text\":\"Knowledge sharing posed the greatest challenge. The majority of the information startups need is topical, specific to their industry, stage and product. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe Hub therefore needed to address the need for both startup specific, and generic content. To achieve this, we\\u2019ve started to develop a mentor matching scheme to pair startups with relevant advisors. \\r\\n\\r\\nMeanwhile, we\\u2019ve also developed a number of tools to share best practices around some of the steps almost all startups follow.  From raising funds to gaining the very first customers.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"49\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Widening The Hub\\u2019s Reach\",\"text\":\"Today, the Hub is the largest startup recruitment site in Denmark. And, we\\u2019re now applying what we\\u2019ve learned across the Nordics, launching Hubs in Norway and Sweden, opening up opportunities for cross-country applications in markets where Danske Bank is most active.\",\"image\":[\"251\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"166\":{\"type\":\"videoBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"youtubeVideoId\":\"V3RTOLI33Q0\"}}},\"80\":\"1\",\"72\":[\"36\"],\"67\":\"We have partnered with Rainmaking because of their strong foothold in the global startup ecosystem, and their impressive ability to launch and grow new platforms and services at high speed\",\"69\":\"Head of Business Innovation\",\"68\":\"Klavs Hjort\",\"71\":[\"22\"]}}', '2016-11-01 09:25:35', '2016-11-01 09:25:35', '285da3e2-976e-40a9-bbd1-c8f6825afdbb'),
 ('266', '7', '7', '15', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Who We Are\",\"slug\":\"who-we-are\",\"postDate\":1477583928,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"63\":\"Everyone at Rainmaking lives and breaths the entrepreneurial spirit. We started in 2006 as a collective of serial entrepreneurs, sharing in the both the risks and the rewards of starting new businesses. Since then, we have grown into a global community of entrepreneurs, investors and ex-corporate executives. Driven to create something new, to make a difference.  \"}}', '2016-11-01 09:42:51', '2016-11-01 09:42:51', 'e64af10f-db3a-4272-ada7-676e1856f1f5'),
 ('267', '282', '8', '15', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"8\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Jakob Kistorp\",\"slug\":\"jakob-kistorp\",\"postDate\":1477661160,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"66\":\"\",\"1\":\"<p>Jakob has&nbsp;globally sourced thousands of startups for clients, helped build and run accelerators, and delivered&nbsp;projects in over 15 countries. He specializes in helping cities and countries to establish and grow self-sustaining startup ecosystems. He co-founded Startup MENA, leading to increased startup funding and the&nbsp;creation of hundreds of new&nbsp;jobs across 9 countries in the region.<\\/p>\",\"65\":\"https:\\/\\/dk.linkedin.com\\/in\\/jakobkistorp\",\"82\":[\"285\"],\"81\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/Kistorp\"}}', '2016-11-01 09:43:43', '2016-11-01 09:43:43', '94a0191c-6d74-421d-a05b-84ed8ed4a733'),
 ('268', '277', '8', '15', 'en_us', '4', '', '{\"typeId\":\"8\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Jordan Schlipf\",\"slug\":\"jordan-schlipf\",\"postDate\":1477590720,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"66\":\"\",\"1\":\"<p>Jordan is an entrepreneur, investor, and educator. He has been&nbsp;both a VC and angel investor and has launched companies in multiple verticals and markets.&nbsp;Jordan is an expert in Lean Startup and design thinking, and has created educational programs for accelerators, universities, corporates and governments. He now leads our venture studio, building multiple new&nbsp;startups&nbsp;in parallel,&nbsp;alongside our fortune 500 partners.<\\/p>\",\"65\":\"https:\\/\\/uk.linkedin.com\\/in\\/jordan-schlipf-0b855174\",\"82\":[\"278\"],\"81\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/jordups\"}}', '2016-11-01 09:45:13', '2016-11-01 09:45:13', '61817dd9-e9d1-4874-9308-6a83a20c4865'),
 ('269', '255', '8', '15', 'en_us', '6', '', '{\"typeId\":\"8\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Nektarios Liolios\",\"slug\":\"nektarios-liolios\",\"postDate\":1477582860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"66\":\"\",\"1\":\"<p>Nektarios has over eleven years\\u2019&nbsp;experience in the banking and financial sector. While working for SWIFT\\u2019s&nbsp;Innotribe he&nbsp;facilitated interactions between startups and financial institutions. Nektarios continues this today,&nbsp;leading our global&nbsp;Startupbootcamp FinTech & InsurTech activities which connect over 30 financial institutions with hundreds of startups each year.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"65\":\"https:\\/\\/uk.linkedin.com\\/in\\/nekliolios\",\"82\":[\"287\"],\"81\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/nekliolios\"}}', '2016-11-01 10:03:48', '2016-11-01 10:03:48', 'b41d2f7f-900d-40e4-8b3f-2dd9c18b1a90'),
 ('270', '275', '8', '15', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"8\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Kasper Vardrup\",\"slug\":\"kasper-vardrup\",\"postDate\":1477589100,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"66\":\"\",\"1\":\"<p>Kasper is a serial tech entrepreneur with six successful startups, one IPO and three exits behind him.&nbsp;Kasper worked as Senior Consultant at Quartz+Co, and has&nbsp;been a director and board member of several private and public companies. Kasper&nbsp;uses his expertise&nbsp;in&nbsp;rapid new business creation and user experience design by building digital products in collaboration with our corporate partners, startup style.<\\/p>\",\"65\":\"https:\\/\\/dk.linkedin.com\\/in\\/kaspervardrup\",\"82\":[\"274\"],\"81\":\"\"}}', '2016-11-01 10:05:15', '2016-11-01 10:05:15', '98f0a72a-5acf-4d04-a494-c51c771cf488'),
 ('271', '254', '8', '15', 'en_us', '4', '', '{\"typeId\":\"8\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Alex Farcet\",\"slug\":\"alex-farcet\",\"postDate\":1477582440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"66\":\"\",\"1\":\"<p>Alex spent over twelve years in management positions with DHL and Deutsche Post until he had a realization that completely changed his perspective on taking risk and living with purpose. Since then, Alex&nbsp;has founded six companies, including Startupbootcamp, where he has personally helped thousands of entrepreneurs launch their own businesses.<\\/p>\",\"65\":\"https:\\/\\/dk.linkedin.com\\/in\\/alexfarcet \",\"82\":[\"279\"],\"81\":\"\"}}', '2016-11-01 10:05:35', '2016-11-01 10:05:35', '03817955-aa54-4040-8f1b-ca9ab3fd295e'),
 ('272', '254', '8', '15', 'en_us', '5', '', '{\"typeId\":\"8\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Alex Farcet\",\"slug\":\"alex-farcet\",\"postDate\":1477582440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"66\":\"\",\"1\":\"<p>Alex spent over twelve years in management positions with DHL and Deutsche Post until he had a realization that completely changed his perspective on taking risk and living with purpose. Since then, Alex&nbsp;has founded six companies, including Startupbootcamp, where he has personally helped thousands of entrepreneurs launch their own businesses.<\\/p>\",\"65\":\"https:\\/\\/dk.linkedin.com\\/in\\/alexfarcet \",\"82\":[\"279\"],\"81\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/alexfarcet\"}}', '2016-11-01 10:06:26', '2016-11-01 10:06:26', 'f971cca6-b950-441f-acb7-b226084054ae'),
 ('273', '253', '15', '15', 'en_us', '5', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Partnership Index\",\"slug\":\"partnership-index\",\"postDate\":1477578627,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"63\":\"Innovation defies definition. It\\u2019s as unique, complex and thrilling as every business we\\u2019ve ever worked with. If years of experience have taught us one thing, it\\u2019s this: the best definition of innovation is to find your own.  \\r\\n\\r\\nWe can help you do that. We have partnered with organizations around the world to cultivate innovative cultures, collaboratively build new products and services, and engage with a global startup community. \"}}', '2016-11-01 10:34:25', '2016-11-01 10:34:25', 'bc7ee608-11dd-4164-a25f-746bb0e1527e'),
 ('274', '69', '4', '15', 'en_us', '12', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Taking Castrol Beyond Motor Oil\",\"slug\":\"strategically-sourcing-startups-to-catapult-castrols-business-forward\",\"postDate\":1477395000,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"64\"],\"47\":{\"74\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Going Beyond Motor Oil\",\"text\":\"In 2012, we were approached by Castrol innoVentures to help increase its deal flow and strengthen its presence and visibility in the global startup community.\\u00a0\\r\\n\\r\\nAt the time, Castrol had just set up its strategic innovation and investment arm in order to bring additional value to its existing business areas, and to take Castrol beyond motor oils and lubricants and into future focused revenue streams.\\r\\n\\r\\nTogether with the team at Castrol innoVentures, we designed a global pitch competition to act as a sourcing and screening program, allowing us to meet and evaluate startups relevant for Castrol to work with. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe program resulted in Castrol making a direct investment in one startup and commercial partnerships with seven others. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"71\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"we were approached by Castrol innoVentures to help increase its deal flow and strengthen its presence and visibility in the global startup community.\\\"\",\"image\":[\"68\"]}},\"72\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"How to Put Castrol On the Global Startup Map\",\"text\":\"In today\\u2019s venture capital environment, startups are not short on sources of investment. There are hundreds of institutional firms, angel investors and CVC\\u2019s. \\r\\n\\r\\nWe needed a way to put Castrol on startups\\u2019 radar as a valuable partner, both to work with, and to have on their cap table. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe focus was for us to find startups innovating in 4 strategic areas: Smart Mobility, next generation engineering, intelligent operations, and responsible Castrol.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"75\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Building a Startup Friendly Brand\",\"text\":\"We built a brand around the project: the Castrol 20\\/20 Challenge. \\r\\n\\r\\nA selection of startup finalists would receive free flights and accommodation to London or Shanghai in order to pitch their business to Venture Capitalists and Castrol executives. The winning team was to receive 10,000 USD.\\r\\n\\r\\nA brand website was launched, promoting the competition to potential applicants and spreading the word throughout the global startup community. Both the brand and website were fundamental in positioning Castrol as a company ready to make investments and meaningfully engage with startups.\",\"image\":[\"73\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"76\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Over 2,000 Startups Reviewed\",\"text\":\"With our marketing efforts driving competition applications, and outreach from our dedicated sourcing team, we attracted and reviewed over 2,000 startups.\\r\\n\\r\\nDrawing on our experience mentoring and selecting startups for our Startupbootcamp programs and our own investments, we created a shortlist of 20 companies based on their applications and 1-1 interviews.\\r\\n\\r\\nTogether with Castrol innoVentures, we conducted further interviews to narrow the selection to just five startups in each of two competition finals in London and Shanghai.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"77\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Preparing Startups for Collaboration with Corporates\",\"text\":\"In both London and Shanghai, we worked with the startups and mentors one day prior to the final events to prepare the teams. We helped them hone their pitches and introduced ways that they could more effectively work with major corporations.  \\r\\n\\r\\nThe following day, the startups pitched and met with over 30 Venture Capitalists, alongside executives from Castrol and other notable corporations like 3M.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe events not only provided immense value to the startups, in terms of connections and networking with experts, but also gave Castrol a platform to engage with the startups early on.\",\"image\":[\"67\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"82\":{\"type\":\"imageBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"images\":[\"79\",\"80\",\"81\"]}},\"78\":{\"type\":\"quoteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"Castrol 2020 Challenge provided impressive and innovative ideas and we work with 7 out of 10 teams from the 2012 program\\\"\",\"quoteName\":\"Roy Williamson\",\"role\":\"Castrol InnoVentures, Managing Director\",\"image\":[\"66\"]}},\"83\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Creating and Capitalising on Investment Opportunities\",\"text\":\"Castrol InnoVentures ultimately invested in Greensteam, a ground breaking technology company specialising in energy saving solutions for commercial vessels.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe events proved to be a success, so we hosted a second edition, this time exclusively in Shanghai.\\r\\n\\r\\nTo this day, Castrol innoVentures remains an active player in the mobility space and has made further investments in a range of startups.\\r\\n\",\"image\":[\"65\"],\"align\":\"left\"}}},\"80\":\"1\",\"72\":[\"65\"],\"67\":\"The Castrol 20\\/20 Challenge provided impressive and innovative ideas leading to us working with 7 out of 10 startups from the program\",\"69\":\"Managing Director, Castrol InnoVentures\",\"68\":\"Roy Williamson\",\"71\":[\"260\"]}}', '2016-11-01 10:36:17', '2016-11-01 10:36:17', '0c0c8192-741f-4ae9-af25-a6d3ca257731'),
 ('275', '195', '4', '15', 'en_us', '7', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"New Ways of Working for Lloyd\'s Banking Group \",\"slug\":\"how-lloyds-banking-group-stays-ahead-of-fintech-evolution\",\"postDate\":1477478580,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"178\"],\"47\":{\"196\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Partnering With Market Leaders\",\"text\":\"Since 2014 we have been helping to shape the global evolution of FinTech. Together with market leaders like MasterCard, Lloyds Banking Group, Santander, Thomson Reuters, PWC and Rabobank we run Startupbootcamp accelerator programs, design corporate innovation programs, and establish commercial connections between startups and established players.\",\"image\":[\"180\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"198\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"Each year we scout upwards of 3000 FinTech startups from across the globe. With accelerator programs in Singapore, London and New York, and 50+ FinTech events across almost every continent. \",\"image\":[\"179\"]}},\"199\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Early Access to Innovation\",\"text\":\"We select less than 1% of these startups for a Startupbootcamp cohort. This ensures our partners are collaborating with the best talent, often generating pilots, commercial partnerships and co-created solutions. Meanwhile, through the selection process itself, partners are exposed to evolving technology and business model trends at an early stage.  \",\"image\":[\"181\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"200\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Staying in Front of the Curve with Lloyd\'s \",\"text\":\"Lloyds Banking Group has been a partner on our Startupbootcamp FinTech program since 2014. The partnership came at a time when the bank was undertaking a large-scale digital transformation program, and presented an ideal platform to test new ideas and connect with the wider FinTech ecosystem. \",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"201\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"Lloyds\\u2019 goal is to scan the market for innovation and find new opportunities to provide better service to their customers. The relationship is beneficial for both parties: the FinTech startup has access to subject matter experts, launching customers and scarce assets like data sets. For Lloyds it is beneficial because they are able to learn about new technology, business models, see the results within the market and deduce important lessons to stay ahead and deliver value to their customers. \",\"image\":[\"182\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"202\":{\"type\":\"quoteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"The relationship with Startupbootcamp has been the first step towards collaborating with startups and to support our digital transformation agenda. By working with innovative partners we are able to deliver even better customer propositions and services.\",\"quoteName\":\"Claire Calmejane\",\"role\":\"Head of Innovation\",\"image\":[\"189\"]}},\"203\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"Collaborating with Startupbootcamp alumni WoraPay \\u2013 is said to have saved Lloyds Banking Group employees 10,000 days of work. \",\"image\":[\"185\"]}},\"204\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"New Ways of Working\",\"text\":\"For Lloyds, collaborating with the FinTech sector also provides inspiring examples of agility and working practices that refresh Lloyd\\u2019s thinking and approach to delivering digital services. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe partnership gave Lloyds the chance to be involved in dedicated events such as FinTech Lounges and hackathons, presenting another opportunity to experience new ways of working.\\r\\n\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"205\":{\"type\":\"imageBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"images\":[\"191\",\"193\",\"194\"]}}},\"80\":\"1\",\"72\":[\"179\"],\"67\":\"Our relationship with Rainmaking has given hundreds of our employees access to new tools and skillsets that they have used to become inspiring intrepreneurs inside Lloyds Banking Group.\\r\\n\",\"69\":\"Head of Innovation\",\"68\":\"Claire Calmejane\",\"71\":[\"189\"]}}', '2016-11-01 10:37:34', '2016-11-01 10:37:34', '4854890b-d979-4fe9-9234-a350e0d30317'),
