 ('301', '237', '5', '1', 'en_us', '8', '', '{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Video: Who Are Rainmaking?\",\"slug\":\"who-are-rainmaking\",\"postDate\":1477558860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"16\":[\"15\"],\"18\":[\"224\"],\"17\":[\"shortForm\"],\"19\":\"\",\"15\":\"<p>Rainmaking Innovation partner, Nektarios Liolios explains what we are all about here at Rainmaking and gives an inside look into some of the ways that we are approaching corporate innovation.<\\/p><div class=\\\"video-container\\\"><iframe src=\\\"\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/embed\\/c9Y0Zlm1Puc\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\" allowfullscreen=\\\"\\\"><\\/iframe><\\/div>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Read the full transcript below.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h1>Interview with Nektarios Liolios<\\/h1>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>My name is Nektarios Liolios, I\'m one of the partners of Rainmaking Innovation.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>What we do a Rainmaking Innovation is we help corporates find ways to innovate, as simple as that.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>People joke about the Kodak moments but, there is a Kodak moment.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The frustration that we see is organizations who are so conservative they actually don\'t understand that if they don\'t move faster they\'re actually running a real risk of failing, of disappearing.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The biggest challenge corporates face with innovation is that they actually don\'t know&nbsp;what they\'re doing. They get very excited, they also feel a lot of pressure to do something and then they randomly do things.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>One of the trends that we see, is organizations recognizing that working with startups is one channel but building products startup style is another, so the trend is really focusing on closing that loop. That\'s one of the things we see, the other one is really diversification. So, looking at innovation, not a box ticking exercise, but it\'s something that has to have many different iterations and many different facets.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>On the positive side, we see organizations trying a variety of different things; setting up their own investment funds, working with accelerators, doing their own incubation initiatives, having very structured programs for themselves. But also, putting a lot of effort into internal innovation initiatives by educating people about change, by giving them the opportunity to see other ways of working by giving them the opportunity to collaborate with competitors.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The smart organizations recognize that they need to do multiple things at the same time and they need to allow themselves to fail. They also need to connect the internal and external innovation efforts. If you just take startup engagement for instance; startups come in different stages and they have different needs and also different benefits for the organization. So, you can be part of an accelerator to see very early stage startups, to get excited by the the spirit and the drive and the passion of entrepreneurs, but also just to see the very latest trends.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When it comes to using real technology that has been built by startups then you have to look at something that is maybe a little bit more advanced, maybe a little bit more mature, but that engagement has to be different. Maybe it\'s more like a managed lab, maybe it\'s trying to find ways of incorporating the technology into the business. And this is something that often happens by exploring. By using something like a startup studio, something like a separate entity, separate organization, that is bringing people together with startup experience and putting them together with project people from the organization who know about the business.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The interesting thing in this new and evolving landscape is that organizations still sometimes cling on to the idea of \\u201cwe have to do everything ourselves,\\u201d and the smarter organizations recognize that there\'s certain things that you cannot do as a bank, as an insurer, as a large corporate by yourself. Because you don\'t have the know how, you don\'t have the expertise; but also, when It comes to collaboration, which is really important in this space, you usually cannot easily collaborate, by yourself, with other parties. So, having a neutral organization, having somebody like a startupbootcamp who would come in the middle, who brings people around the table and gets them to openly share their challenges, share their problems and priorities, and get them to jointly engage with startups is something that we\'ve seen being very successful.<\\/p>\"}}', '2016-11-10 10:59:35', '2016-11-10 10:59:35', '96304385-3df8-4ffa-bfa7-3d8a18ac518a'),
 ('302', '253', '15', '1', 'en_us', '6', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Innovation defies definition.\",\"slug\":\"partnership-index\",\"postDate\":1477578627,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"63\":\"It\\u2019s as unique, complex and thrilling as every business we\\u2019ve ever worked with. If years of experience have taught us one thing, it\\u2019s this: the best definition of innovation is to find your own.  \\r\\n\\r\\nWe can help you do that. We have partnered with organizations around the world to cultivate innovative cultures, collaboratively build new products and services, and engage with a global startup community. \"}}', '2016-11-14 11:37:47', '2016-11-14 11:37:47', '70e89c1b-596f-4553-8478-7facc15e4ee1'),
 ('303', '9', '10', '1', 'en_us', '9', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Europe\'s largest startup accelerator\",\"slug\":\"accelerator\",\"postDate\":1476725058,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Since we founded Startupbootcamp in 2006, it\\u2019s become one of the world\\u2019s leading,&nbsp;industry specific accelerator programs, driving collaboration between startups and corporate partners&nbsp;across entire ecosystems. To date we have 16 programs in 13 cities across the globe with a presence in every major geography. Startups come to us looking for the right partners, investors and mentors to take the next step forward. Our corporate partners come to us to find the next big thing and gain access to a global network.<\\/p>\",\"73\":[\"310\"],\"93\":\"\"}}', '2016-11-14 11:41:59', '2016-11-14 11:41:59', '96d8ece2-1dae-41f2-bc61-dc4c3db4eca4'),
 ('304', '8', '9', '1', 'en_us', '4', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"We practise what we preach\",\"slug\":\"companies\",\"postDate\":1476725045,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Creating companies and bringing them to market is our first love. Together, we\\u2019ve built over 25 of our own startups, achieved 5 notable exits and participated in more than 350 investments. Here are just a few active companies that we have built.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"73\":[\"20\"],\"93\":\"\"}}', '2016-11-14 11:42:22', '2016-11-14 11:42:22', 'd72894fa-4408-42b0-8d3a-1648aa9dc346'),
 ('305', '10', '11', '1', 'en_us', '5', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Building spaces to connect and learn\",\"slug\":\"spaces\",\"postDate\":1476725070,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Over the last ten years, we have created a global community of startups, bringing entrepreneurs, investors and corporate partners together. Our co-working spaces in Berlin, Copenhagen and London are now home to over 1,000 entrepreneurs \\u2013 and there\\u2019s always room for new arrivals. Expect hackathons, lively debates, new ideas and networking events with industry and government figures.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"73\":[\"19\"],\"93\":\"\"}}', '2016-11-14 11:42:47', '2016-11-14 11:42:47', '9f905d79-afdf-4668-8f9c-9dd11cf3f641'),
 ('306', '129', '4', '1', 'en_us', '4', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Sourcing Europe\'s Best EdTech Startups for Collaboration With Sanoma\",\"slug\":\"sourcing-europes-best-edtech-startups-for-collaboration-with-sanoma\",\"postDate\":1477412460,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"127\"],\"91\":\"\",\"47\":{\"130\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Strategic Deal Flow: A Win-Win\",\"text\":\"For this project we were entrusted with finding hopeful EdTech startups with the potential to grow their business together with Sanoma, the Nordic region\\u2019s leading media and learning company.\\r\\n\\r\\nPromising startups were invited to participate in the \\u201cSanoma Startup Challenge - the future of learning,\\u201d an event which we designed and delivered to discover promising startup talent.\",\"image\":[\"122\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"131\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"The Future of Learning\",\"text\":\"Sanoma Ventures came to us looking for ways to find high quality deal flow for their newly formed corporate venture fund. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe media and education space has been making a steady shift away from traditional print and television to new models of delivery and distribution. Seeing the trend, Sanoma sought to partner and invest in startups that could provide different ways to reach students, distribute information and produce content.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"132\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"5 Converge to Compete in Amsterdam\",\"text\":\"Using our existing networks through our Startupbootcamp programs and dedicated research team we began surveying Europe for startups that could supply innovative shifts in Sanoma\\u2019s  business model.\\r\\n\\r\\nOur efforts spanned 22 European countries. We evaluated over 500 startups, encouraging over 100 high quality applications. From these, we hand-picked the best 50 to participate in the challenge.\\r\\nThe top 5 teams won an all-expenses paid trip to Amsterdam for the competition Final.\",\"image\":[\"123\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"133\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"Our efforts spanned 22 European countries. We evaluated over 500 startups, encouraging over 100 high quality applications. From these, we hand-picked the best 50 to participate in the challenge.\\\"\",\"image\":[\"123\"]}},\"134\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"The two-day competition offered startups the chance to work with mentors, Sanoma executives, Sanoma Learning industry experts and SanomaVenture\\u2019s investment team. \\r\\n\\r\\nBy exposing startups to these potential partners and customers, we pushed them to evolve their ideas, while demonstrating the potential benefits of collaboration between corporations and startups.\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"135\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Value for Both Sides of the Table\",\"text\":\"As a part of the Sanoma Startup Challenge, the startups were given the opportunity to make their final pitch at THENEXTWEB conference in Amsterdam, live on stage in front of Sanoma executives, investors and the full conference crowd.\\r\\n\\r\\nUltimately, a Danish startup, Labster, which offers next generation laboratory simulations, was named the winner, receiving a cash prize of \\u20ac25,000.\\r\\n\\r\\nTo date, Sanoma has invested in 18 different ed-tech startups.\",\"image\":[\"124\"],\"align\":\"right\"}}},\"80\":\"\",\"72\":[\"124\"],\"100\":\"Get in touch\",\"99\":\"Ready to talk about what innovation means for you?\",\"67\":\"We were pleasantly surprised by the diversity and the high quality of the startups that applied ... the challenge has already given us interesting new connections for both SanomaVentures, for potential investments, as for Sanoma Learning for future cooperation and partnerships\",\"69\":\"Herman Kienhuis\",\"68\":\"Investment Director\",\"71\":[\"225\"]}}', '2016-11-14 13:06:36', '2016-11-14 13:06:36', 'c6ec22fb-7f3f-426d-af16-58dad0e09384'),
 ('307', '195', '4', '15', 'en_us', '8', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"New Ways of Working for Lloyd\'s Banking Group \",\"slug\":\"how-lloyds-banking-group-stays-ahead-of-fintech-evolution\",\"postDate\":1477478580,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"178\"],\"91\":\"\",\"47\":{\"196\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Partnering With Market Leaders\",\"text\":\"<p>Since 2014 we have been helping to shape the global evolution of FinTech. Together with market leaders like MasterCard, Lloyds Banking Group, Santander, Thomson Reuters, PWC and Rabobank we run Startupbootcamp accelerator programs, design corporate innovation programs, and establish commercial connections between startups and established players.<\\/p>\",\"image\":[\"180\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"198\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"Each year we scout upwards of 3000 FinTech startups from across the globe. With accelerator programs in Singapore, London and New York, and 50+ FinTech events across almost every continent. \",\"image\":[\"179\"]}},\"199\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Early Access to Innovation\",\"text\":\"<p>We select less than 1% of these startups for a Startupbootcamp cohort. This ensures our partners are collaborating with the best talent, often generating pilots, commercial partnerships and co-created solutions. Meanwhile, through the selection process itself, partners are exposed to evolving technology and business model trends at an early stage.<\\/p>\",\"image\":[\"181\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"200\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Staying in Front of the Curve with Lloyd\'s \",\"text\":\"<p>Lloyds Banking Group has been a partner on our Startupbootcamp FinTech program since 2014. The partnership came at a time when the bank was undertaking a large-scale digital transformation program, and presented an ideal platform to test new ideas and connect with the wider FinTech ecosystem.<\\/p>\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"201\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\",\"text\":\"<p>Lloyds\\u2019 goal is to scan the market for innovation and find new opportunities to provide better service to their customers. The relationship is beneficial for both parties: the FinTech startup has access to subject matter experts, launching customers and scarce assets like data sets. For Lloyds it is beneficial because they are able to learn about new technology, business models, see the results within the market and deduce important lessons to stay ahead and deliver value to their customers.<\\/p>\",\"image\":[\"182\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"202\":{\"type\":\"quoteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"The relationship with Startupbootcamp has been the first step towards collaborating with startups and to support our digital transformation agenda. By working with innovative partners we are able to deliver even better customer propositions and services.\",\"quoteName\":\"Claire Calmejane\",\"role\":\"Head of Innovation\",\"image\":[\"189\"]}},\"203\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"Collaborating with Startupbootcamp alumni WoraPay \\u2013 is said to have saved Lloyds Banking Group employees 10,000 days of work. \",\"image\":[\"185\"]}},\"204\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"New Ways of Working\",\"text\":\"<p>For Lloyds, collaborating with the FinTech sector also provides inspiring examples of agility and working practices that refresh Lloyd\\u2019s thinking and approach to delivering digital services. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The partnership gave Lloyds the chance to be involved in dedicated events such as FinTech Lounges and hackathons, presenting another opportunity to experience new ways of working.<\\/p>\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"205\":{\"type\":\"imageBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"images\":[\"191\",\"193\",\"194\"]}}},\"80\":\"1\",\"72\":[\"179\"],\"100\":\"\",\"99\":\"\",\"67\":\"Our relationship with Rainmaking has given hundreds of our colleagues access to new tools and new ways of working that they are using to become inspiring intrapreneurs and to develop new propositions and services for our customers\\r\\n\",\"69\":\"Director of Innovation\",\"68\":\"Claire Calmejane\",\"71\":[\"189\"]}}', '2016-11-14 16:59:12', '2016-11-14 16:59:12', 'e86fbc20-66c3-42e3-a992-3125e3d60d64'),
 ('308', '2', '1', '15', 'en_us', '27', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Homepage\",\"slug\":\"homepage\",\"postDate\":1476710702,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"75\":[\"18\"],\"4\":\"We created Startupbootcamp \\u2014 the largest industry focused accelerator network in the world with 16 programs across five continents. \",\"76\":[\"20\"],\"6\":\"We have built 25 of our own startups, achieving 5 notable exits and lead over 350 startup investments. \",\"9\":[\"195\",\"69\",\"24\",\"57\"],\"3\":\"Partner with proven entrepreneurs. Harness startup behaviors that complement what you\\u2019re doing already. And introduce you to what you should be doing.\",\"11\":\"We live in a world that is changing faster than ever.\\u00a0Where past performance is no guarantee of future success. We know from experience\\u00a0that no matter how well you plan\\u00a0new ventures,\\u00a0sometimes they just don\\u2019t work. This is part of our approach to\\u00a0helping our partners discover innovation for\\u00a0their own organizations. If something works \\u2013 or if it doesn\\u2019t \\u2013 you\\u2019ll know about it.   Many claim to have the answers but\\u00a0hide behind powerpoint presentations and buzzwords. We accept that we don\'t have all the answers, but we do know the right questions to ask.\\u00a0  Read the\\u00a0latest thoughts and lessons learned\\u00a0from experts across the Rainmaking community.\\u00a0\",\"89\":\"Nektarios Liolios\",\"90\":[\"287\"],\"78\":[\"56\"],\"88\":[\"292\",\"293\",\"295\",\"298\",\"301\",\"305\",\"304\",\"299\"],\"7\":\"We partner with organizations to deliver training. Engage with startups. Build digital products and launch new ventures.\",\"12\":\"We love results, not presentations. \",\"8\":\"We give you the mindset, skills and confidence to ideate, create and scale new business.   Collaboratively and confidently. No buzzwords. Just plain English.  \\r\\nAnd we\\u2019ll make sure it happens. We love results not presentations. Actions not words. \\r\\n\\r\\nJust see for yourself.\",\"77\":[\"19\"],\"5\":\"We created Rainmaking Loft coworking spaces. Serving over 1,000 entrepreneurs in London, Berlin and Copenhagen.\"}}', '2016-11-14 17:02:47', '2016-11-14 17:02:47', '6a9073da-3d00-4fd5-be22-4888018bff61'),
 ('309', '10', '11', '15', 'en_us', '6', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Building spaces to connect and learn\",\"slug\":\"spaces\",\"postDate\":1476725070,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Over the last ten years, we have created a global community of startups, bringing entrepreneurs, investors and corporate partners together. Our co-working spaces in Berlin, Copenhagen and London are now home to over 1,000 entrepreneurs \\u2013 and there\\u2019s always room for new arrivals. Expect hackathons, lively debates, new ideas and networking events with industry and government figures.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"73\":[\"19\"],\"93\":\"\"}}', '2016-11-14 17:04:33', '2016-11-14 17:04:33', 'c600aa57-5fe3-485e-88e3-8f80603eccd4');
