>The focus was for us to find startups innovating in 4 strategic areas: Smart Mobility, next generation engineering, intelligent operations, and responsible Castrol.<\\/p>\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"75\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Building a Startup Friendly Brand\",\"text\":\"<p>We built a brand around the project: the Castrol 20\\/20 Challenge.<\\/p><p>A selection of startup finalists would receive free flights and accommodation to London or Shanghai in order to pitch their business to Venture Capitalists and Castrol executives. The winning team was to receive 10,000 USD.<\\/p><p><span><\\/span>A brand website was launched, promoting the competition to potential applicants and spreading the word throughout the global startup community. Both the brand and website were fundamental in positioning Castrol as a company ready to make investments and meaningfully engage with startups.<\\/p>\",\"image\":[\"73\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"76\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Over 2,000 Startups Reviewed\",\"text\":\"<p>With our marketing efforts driving competition applications, and outreach from our dedicated sourcing team, we attracted and reviewed over 2,000 startups.<\\/p><p>Drawing on our experience mentoring and selecting startups for our Startupbootcamp programs and our own investments, we created a shortlist of 20 companies based on their applications and 1-1 interviews.<\\/p><p><span><\\/span>Together with Castrol innoVentures, we conducted further interviews to narrow the selection to just five startups in each of two competition finals in London and Shanghai.<\\/p>\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"77\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Preparing Startups for Collaboration with Corporates\",\"text\":\"<p>In both London and Shanghai, we worked with the startups and mentors one day prior to the final events to prepare the teams. We helped them hone their pitches and introduced ways that they could more effectively work with major corporations.T<\\/p><p>he following day, the startups pitched and met with over 30 Venture Capitalists, alongside executives from Castrol and other notable corporations like 3M.<\\/p><p><span><\\/span>The events not only provided immense value to the startups, in terms of connections and networking with experts, but also gave Castrol a platform to engage with the startups early on.<\\/p>\",\"image\":[\"67\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"82\":{\"type\":\"imageBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"images\":[\"79\",\"80\",\"81\"]}},\"78\":{\"type\":\"quoteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"Castrol 2020 Challenge provided impressive and innovative ideas and we work with 7 out of 10 teams from the 2012 program\\\"\",\"quoteName\":\"Roy Williamson\",\"role\":\"Castrol InnoVentures, Managing Director\",\"image\":[\"66\"]}},\"83\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Creating and Capitalising on Investment Opportunities\",\"text\":\"<p>Castrol InnoVentures ultimately invested in Greensteam, a ground breaking technology company specialising in energy saving solutions for commercial vessels.<\\/p><p>The events proved to be a success, so we hosted a second edition, this time exclusively in Shanghai.<\\/p><p><span><\\/span>To this day, Castrol innoVentures remains an active player in the mobility space and has made further investments in a range of startups.<\\/p>\",\"image\":[\"65\"],\"align\":\"left\"}}},\"80\":\"1\",\"72\":[\"65\"],\"100\":\"Get in touch\",\"99\":\"Want to learn more about engaging with startups to access innovation?\",\"67\":\"The Castrol 20\\/20 Challenge provided impressive and innovative ideas leading to us working with 7 out of 10 startups from the program\",\"69\":\"Managing Director\",\"68\":\"Roy Williamson\",\"71\":[\"260\"]}}', '2016-11-15 10:44:20', '2016-11-15 10:44:20', '61cc2960-ed6e-4614-