 ('373', '246', '3', '15', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"The Rainmaking Sessions - Disruptive InsurTech: From now to 2030\",\"slug\":\"the-rainmaking-sessions-disruptive-insurtech-from-now-to-2030\",\"postDate\":1477571040,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"25\":\"1 St. Katherine\'s Way, London, E1W 1UN\",\"1\":\"<p>For years FinTech has dominating with news of investments, advancements and innovation. However, the industry on everyone\\u2019s radar for 2016 is insurance. In order to examine these developments, Rainmaking Innovations, in association with Startupbootcamp InsurTech, invite you to an exclusive breakfast roundtable event looking at digital disruption in insurance.<\\/p><p><em>Disruptive InsurTech: From now to 2030 - What will your path to success be?<\\/em>&nbsp;will be an interactive, think tank style roundtable where you can hear from industry experts to debate and discuss the current state of the industry as well as future trends with your peers.<\\/p><p><span><\\/span>You will hear from:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Sabine VanderLinden, MD Startupbootcamp InsurTech<\\/li><li>Carolina Vicente,&nbsp;Director of Digital Marketing, Google<\\/li><li>Moderated by: Liz Lumley, Rainmaking Innovation<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Please join us at the Rainmaking Loft to be a part of the first of a series of thought provoking Rainmaking Sessions looking at innovation and disruptive trends.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>When:&nbsp;28 October 2016<\\/li><li>Where:&nbsp;The Rainmaking Loft, 1 St Katherine\\u2019s Way, London E1W 4UN<\\/li><li>Agenda:<\\/li><li>9:00 - Arrival at loft for coffee<\\/li><li>9:15 - Buffet style breakfast served<\\/li><li>9:45 - Welcome and talks begin<\\/li><li>10:15 - Moderated Roundtable starts<\\/li><li>11:30 - Breakfast Roundtable ends<\\/li><\\/ul><p><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">Spaces are limited, so please RSVP&nbsp;for your chance to be a part of this special event.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"23\":\"https:\\/\\/www.eventbrite.co.uk\\/e\\/disruptive-insurtech-from-now-to-2030-registration-26699864012\",\"73\":[\"182\"],\"24\":\"Rainmaking Loft - London\",\"26\":{\"date\":\"10\\/28\\/2016\",\"time\":\"9:00 AM\"}}}', '2016-11-15 18:01:06', '2016-11-15 18:01:06', '8ebca6b0-bec8-4425-8ca9-2da5dfe96553'),
 ('374', '245', '3', '15', 'en_us', '7', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"The Rainmaking Sessions  - Innovation in the financial supply chain\",\"slug\":\"innovation-in-the-financial-supply-chain\",\"postDate\":1477570200,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"25\":\"1 St. Katherine\'s Way, London, E1W 1UN\",\"1\":\"<p>Innovation in the financial supply chain&nbsp;\\u2013&nbsp;<em>How can banks find opportunities for innovation in the changing face of the supply chain?<\\/em><\\/p><p><em><\\/em>In the post-digital, global economy, corporate and commercial clients are both importers and exporters; supply chains are deeper and more fragmented and access to trade credit is being squeezed. The International Chamber of Commerce (ICC) Standard Definitions for Techniques of Supply Chain Finance pave the way for greater adoption and commonality in supply chain finance and bank assisted open account offerings.<\\/p><p><span><\\/span>Supply chains for many of your corporate clients are multi-layered and complex, with difficulties in obtaining visibility, connectivity or sufficient risk information across all parties involved. Visibility of the so-called \\u201clong tail\\u201d is crucial for reducing transaction risk. In many areas, supply chains are getting shorter and they need to be dynamic, fast, agile and data-centric. The emergence of cloud platforms, new marketplaces, eDocs and new standards now provide the ecosystem for banks and new entrants to revolutionise the market. But collaboration is king.<\\/p><p><span><\\/span><em>Innovation in the financial supply chain<\\/em>, will be an interactive, think tank style roundtable, sponsored by Misys. Industry experts and supply chain professionals will debate and discuss the current state of the industry as well as future trends.Please join us at the Rainmaking Loft to be a part of this series of thought-provoking Rainmaking Sessions, on trends that are shaping our industry.<\\/p><p><span><\\/span>You will hear from:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Tom Ward, Head of Finance - Supply Chain at Tesco PLC<\\/li><li>Mike Walker, Head of Product Management, Open Account&nbsp;& Supply Chain Finance,&nbsp;<\\/li><\\/ul><p><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">MisysAgenda:<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>8:15 - Arrival at loft for coffee&nbsp;<\\/li><li>8:30 \\u2013 Buffet style breakfast served&nbsp;<\\/li><li>8:45 - Welcome and talks begin&nbsp;<\\/li><li>9:15 - Moderated Roundtable starts&nbsp;<\\/li><li>10:30 - Breakfast Roundtable endsSpaces are limited, so please register for your chance to be a part of this special event.<\\/li><\\/ul><p><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">The Rainmaking Sessions\\r\\n<\\/span><em style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">The Rainmaking Sessions are series of monthly, breakfast roundtables to foster debate, discussion and discourse on the nature of innovation in corporates, FinTech, InsurTech, Digital Health and Smart Transportation.<\\/em><\\/p>\",\"23\":\"https:\\/\\/www.eventbrite.co.uk\\/e\\/innovation-in-the-financial-supply-chain-tickets-28785655671\",\"73\":[\"143\"],\"24\":\"Rainmaking Loft - London\",\"26\":{\"date\":\"12\\/7\\/2016\",\"time\":\"8:00 AM\"}}}', '2016-11-15 18:02:20', '2016-11-15 18:02:20', '933dfa65-7edc-4b67-a58b-6945af0fc362'),
 ('375', '243', '3', '15', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"The Rainmaking Sessions - Playing in the sandbox\",\"slug\":\"the-rainmaking-sessions-playing-in-the-sandbox\",\"postDate\":1477564560,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"25\":\"1 St. Katherine\'s Way, London, E1W 1UN\",\"1\":\"<p>Playing in the sandbox&nbsp;-&nbsp;<em>Can co-creation, between startups and incumbents, be the key to building successful products?<\\/em><\\/p><p><em><\\/em>This year the Financial Conduct Authority launched the Regulatory Sandbox, which is meant to be a \\u2018safe space\\u2019 where businesses can test innovative products, services, business models and delivery mechanisms. This is a progressive step for startups in regulated industries, like financial services. However, many young companies still need active partnerships with established banks, firms and other corporates in order to test developing products with live data, enterprise architecture and an active customer base.Sandboxes, like the one set up by the FCA in the UK, are a step in the right direction for regulated industries. But they struggle to be useful if certain startups aren\\u2019t given the resources to test their products, properly.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>What incentives can you give traditional firms to invite them into the sandbox to support startups to co-create industry-changing products? What procedures can you put in place to make sure co-creation is not only beneficial to startups, incumbents firms but to the regulatory process itself?<\\/p><p><span><\\/span><em>Playing in the sandbox,&nbsp;<\\/em>will be an interactive, think tank style roundtable where you can hear from industry experts to debate and discuss the current state of the industry as well as future trends with your peers.<\\/p><p><span><\\/span>Please join us at the Rainmaking Loft to be a part of this series of thought provoking Rainmaking Sessions, trends that are shaping our industry.<\\/p><p><span><\\/span>You will hear from:&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Anna Wallace,&nbsp;Manager, Innovation Hub at the Financial Conduct Authority\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Jon Pearson, London Lab Manager, Deutsche Bank LabsAgenda:<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>8:15 - Arrival at loft for coffee\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>8:30 \\u2013 Buffet style breakfast served\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>8:45 - Welcome and talks begin\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>9:15 - Moderated Roundtable starts\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><li>10:30 - Breakfast Roundtable ends<\\/li><\\/ul><p><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">Spaces are limited, so please register with EventBrite for your chance to be a part of this special event.<\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\"><\\/span><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">Once you reserve your place, please shout about your attendance by sharing \\u2018I will be adding my views and insights to the #RainmakingSessions on&nbsp;<\\/span><em style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">Playing in the sandbox on 11&nbsp;<\\/em><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">October!\\u2019 on your social media channels.<\\/span><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">The Rainmaking Sessions<\\/span><em style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">The Rainmaking Sessions<\\/em><em style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">&nbsp;are series of monthly, breakfast roundtables to foster debate, discussion and discourse on the nature of innovation in corporates, FinTech, InsurTech, Digital Health and Smart Transportation.<\\/em><\\/p>\",\"23\":\"https:\\/\\/www.eventbrite.co.uk\\/e\\/playing-in-the-sandbox-tickets-27541673888\",\"73\":[\"104\"],\"24\":\"Rainmaking Loft - London\",\"26\":{\"date\":\"10\\/11\\/2016\",\"time\":\"8:00 AM\"}}}', '2016-11-15 18:04:04', '2016-11-15 18:04:04', 'fb5797aa-c134-4b33-969b-c864bcc1858b'),
 ('376', '236', '3', '15', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Shaping the FinTech future for banks and SMEs\",\"slug\":\"shaping-the-fintech-future-for-banks-and-smes\",\"postDate\":1477558560,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"25\":\"1 St. Katherine\'s Way, London, E1W 1UN\",\"1\":\"<p>According to data from the British Bankers Association (BBA) net lending to small to medium sized businesses in the UK reached of \\u00a32.1billion in the last quarter of 2015. Nevertheless, many banks are feeling the pressure from alternative finance and peer-to-peer lenders to meet the growing needs of what some estimate make up around 99% of the UK\\u2019s private sector businesses.<\\/p><p>What strategies are banks using to ease the pace in which credit and loans are made available to these business? Will new alternative providers beat banks in the race for customers? Or will banks look to partner and collaborate with these new FinTech entrants to offer services better matched to the needs of a 21st Century business?<\\/p><p><span><\\/span><em>Shaping the FinTech future for banks and SMEs&nbsp;<\\/em>will be an interactive, think tank style roundtable where you can hear from industry experts to debate and discuss the current state of the industry as well as future trends with your peers.<\\/p><p><span><\\/span>You will hear from:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Justin Hannemann, Head of Product Experience (Customer and Innovation), Santander UK<\\/li><li>Johanna Pugh, global head of Lending, Misys<\\/li><li>Moderation \\u2013 Liz Lumley<\\/li><\\/ul><p>Please join us at the Rainmaking Loft to be a part of this series of thought provoking Rainmaking Sessions, sponsored by Misys, looking at innovative and disruptive trends.<\\/p><p><span><\\/span>Once you reserve your place, please shout about your attendance by sharing \\u2018I will be adding my views and insights to the #RainmakingSessions on&nbsp;<em>Shaping the FinTech future for banks and SMEs&nbsp;<\\/em>14 July<em>&nbsp;<\\/em>2016!\\u2019 on your social media channels.<\\/p><p><em>The Rainmaking Sessions<\\/em><em>&nbsp;are series of monthly, breakfast roundtables to foster debate, discussion and discourse on the nature of innovation in corporates, FinTech, InsurTech, Digital Health and Smart Transportantion and Energy.<\\/em><\\/p>\",\"23\":\"https:\\/\\/www.eventbrite.co.uk\\/e\\/shaping-the-fintech-future-for-banks-and-smes-registration-26034413632\",\"73\":[\"104\"],\"24\":\"Rainmaking Loft - London\",\"26\":{\"date\":\"7\\/14\\/2016\",\"time\":\"8:00 AM\"}}}', '2016-11-15 18:05:21', '2016-11-15 18:05:21', '72955bef-5cdf-4c08-888d-74fe2f8e86d3'),
 ('377', '235', '3', '15', 'en_us', '4', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"The Rainmaking Sessions - What\'s the matter with payments?\",\"slug\":\"the-rainmaking-sessions-whats-the-matter-with-payments\",\"postDate\":1477556940,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"25\":\"1 St. Katherine\'s Way, London, E1W 1UN\",\"1\":\"<p>Startupbootcamp FinTech\\u2019s 2015 Trend Report highlighted a decrease in the volume of quality startups in the payments space. However, around 60% of UK respondents to a PwC Global FinTech survey think consumer banking and payments are going to be the most disrupted sectors over the next five years. Payments used to define what the industry thought of as FinTech disruption. However, new entrants to the market may have underestimated the relative complexity of payments. Will we see a new payments era emerge that is stronger, more mature and, at last, truly disruptive?<em>What\\u2019s the matter with payments?<\\/em>&nbsp;will be an interactive, think tank style roundtable where you can hear from industry experts to debate and discuss the current state of the industry as well as future trends with your peers.<\\/p><p><span><\\/span>You will hear from:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Jon Prideaux, CEO at Boku<\\/li><li>Richard Jackson, UK Managing Director, WoraPay<\\/li><li>Moderation \\u2013 Liz Lumley<\\/li><\\/ul><p><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">Please join us at the&nbsp;Rainmaking Loft&nbsp;to be a part of the Summer Season series of thought provoking&nbsp;Rainmaking Sessions&nbsp;looking at innovation and disruptive trends.<\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">When:&nbsp;16 June 2016\\r\\n\\r\\nWhere:&nbsp;The Rainmaking Loft, 1 St Katherine\\u2019s Way, London E1W 1UN\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nAgenda<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>8:15 - Arrival at loft for coffee<\\/li><li>8:30 \\u2013 Buffet style breakfast served<\\/li><li>8:45 - Welcome and talks begin<\\/li><li>9:15 - Moderated Roundtable starts<\\/li><li>10:30 - Breakfast Roundtable ends<\\/li><\\/ul><p><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">Spaces are limited, so please register now for your chance to be a part of this special event. Once you reserve your place, please shout about your attendance by sharing \\u2018I will be adding my views and insights to the #RainmakingSessions on&nbsp;<\\/span><em style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">What\\u2019s the matter with payments?<\\/em><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">on 16 June 2016!\\u2019 on your social media channels.<\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\"><\\/span><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">The Rainmaking Sessions \\u2013 the Summer Season.<\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\"><\\/span><em style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">The Rainmaking Sessions<\\/em><em style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">&nbsp;are series of monthly, breakfast roundtables to foster debate, discussion and discourse on the nature of innovation in corporates, FinTech, InsurTech, Digital Health and Smart Transportation.<\\/em><em style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">To launch this exclusive, members-only think tank in the heart of London\\u2019s innovation community, three monthly events are planned to liven up the summer season.<\\/em><em style=\\\"background-color: initial;\\\">Attendees will be signed up to a mailing list for information on future Rainmaking Sessions at the Rainmaking Loft. Please indicate if you do not want to be part of this mailing list.&nbsp;<\\/em><\\/p>\",\"23\":\"https:\\/\\/www.eventbrite.co.uk\\/e\\/the-rainmaking-sessions-whats-the-matter-with-payments-tickets-25602215917\",\"73\":[\"104\"],\"24\":\"Rainmaking Loft - London\",\"26\":{\"date\":\"6\\/16\\/2016\",\"time\":\"8:00 AM\"}}}', '2016-11-15 18:07:37', '2016-11-15 18:07:37', '6f853e88-2147-4cdf-964d-2af35e0f9aee'),
 ('378', '57', '4', '15', 'en_us', '14', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"15\",\"title\":\"Finding the Future of Transportation for Daimler\",\"slug\":\"finding-the-future-of-transportation-for-daimler\",\"postDate\":1477393440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"70\":[\"51\"],\"91\":\"Daimler\",\"47\":{\"58\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Finding the Driving Edge of Startup Talent\",\"text\":\"<p>Daimler, a partner of Startupbootcamp Smart Transportation, owner of Mercedes Benz and the largest commercial vehicle manufacturer in the world, came to us looking for startups that could help them gain an edge against competition and stay up to date on emerging technology.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We sourced over 1,000 startups from across 18 countries and identified a number of forces that are shaping the future of transportation and mobility.<\\/p>\",\"image\":[\"50\"],\"align\":\"left\"}},\"252\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"We sourced over 1,000 startups from across 18 countries and identified a number of forces that are shaping the future of transportation and mobility.\\\"\",\"image\":\"\"}},\"59\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Staying In the Fast Lane\",\"text\":\"<p>As cars have become connected, electric and autonomous, Daimler has recognized that they must identify new innovations early in order to stay at the forefront of current technological advancements.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Our challenge was to find the next generation of startups that could help Daimler overtake their competition.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>With this in mind, Daimler asked us to source startup talent, and identify trends that are driving innovation within the smart mobility space.<\\/p>\",\"backgroundColour\":\"grey\"}},\"60\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"\\u00a1Hola Brazil!\",\"text\":\"<p>Our sourcing team screened startups from around the globe. And, identified the most interesting startups for Daimler.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Beginning with a world wide scope, we quickly identified Europe and Brazil as exciting areas for new talent.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Responding to global trends, we saw that Brazil\\u2019s growth had opened up new markets and created untapped opportunities for startups. In particular, urbanization and rapid population growth present problems that startups are actively finding innovative solutions to. This led us to a new hotbed of talent that was generally underrepresented in mainstream sources.<\\/p>\",\"image\":[\"52\"],\"align\":\"right\"}},\"61\":{\"type\":\"soundbyteBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"\\\"Beginning with a world wide scope, we quickly identified Europe and Brazil as exciting areas for new talent.\\\"\",\"image\":[\"212\"]}},\"62\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Getting the Whole Picture\",\"text\":\"<p>At the end of the two month sourcing period we had:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Sourced startups from 87 data sources<\\/li><li>Covered 18 countries<\\/li><li>Reviewed 1759 startups<\\/li><li>Selected 326 startups for further review<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"backgroundColour\":\"black\"}},\"63\":{\"type\":\"textBlockWithImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"header\":\"Delivering Startups, Trends, and Actionable Intel\",\"text\":\"<p>Our internal panel reviewed and assessed these startups, refining the selection to a top 40. These were presented back to Daimler alongside a trend report capturing industry insights, further highlighting opportunities for engagement within the startup world.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Today Daimler remains actively involved in the startup ecosystem, as a partner in our Smart Transportation & Energy Startupbootcamp and continues to pursue new innovations.<\\/p>\",\"image\":[\"54\"],\"align\":\"right\"}}},\"80\":\"1\",\"72\":[\"262\"],\"100\":\"Get in touch\",\"99\":\"Want to keep an eye on developing trends?\",\"67\":\"Partnering with Startupbootcamp will accelerate our access to innovation and will plug us into an impressive community of alumni, mentors and investors\",\"69\":\"Senior Manager, Business Innovation\",\"68\":\"Dr. Frank Spennemann\",\"71\":[\"263\"]}}', '2016-11-15 18:13:10', '2016-11-15 18:13:10', '1d6f5aae-ed0a-4c52-8857-86c08f96a3df'),
