 ('24', 'field', '47', 'en_us', ' people office group team 1 we partnered with danske bank to create thehub dk a platform that aims to relieve the pains of danish startups and provide a platform for danske bank to engage with the startup ecosystem grey participating in the future danske bank came to us in the fall of 2015 with an exciting challenge to create and run a project that would add value to danish startups and accelerate the growth of early stage companies danske bank wanted to test new forms of engagement with emerging businesses by actively participating in the danish startup ecosystem they gain early insights into new technologies and business models that could impact their business in the future by supporting startups at an early stage helping them succeed and grow danske bank also creates a wider stream of potential future customers left an online recruiting platform community and resource center hero frontpage image upload 7136f40d70cf5f2217433b0b8c8efbea after over 100 founder interviews we found three major pain points faced by danish startups recruitment lack of a nationwide startup focused job boardfunding navigating the overwhelming number of investors and funding options to find the right choiceknowledge sharing capitalizing on the experience of successful founders to accelerate progresswith these three problems in mind we created the hub hubchairs with these three problems in mind we created the hub black top tech talent targeting recruitment first we built a job board tailored specifically to startups we found that startups rely on their own networks and traditional job boards for hiring but they were missing something fit for purpose specifically for entrepreneurs targeting job seekers interested in joining startups we ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits converting to 600 weekly applications this is paired with great feedback from both startups and applicants using the site shortcut funding we ve now created over 550 startup profiles and see over 11000 weekly visits converting to 600 weekly applications bonus image upload 0b21db2320eef3b2bafa0e0642919e15 happy hub user we received far more applications through the hub compared to elsewhere all the applicants were relevant and part of our target group for those reasons i would recommend the hub and have already done it right connection with investors shortcut funding to help navigate the funding options available to danish startups our next solution was to create a tool which could match startups with the most relevant options for them based on their industry experience level of maturity and team size this included profiles of the top 50 investors in denmark black access to expert knowledge knowledge sharing posed the greatest challenge the majority of the information startups need is topical specific to their industry stage and product the hub therefore needed to address the need for both startup specific and generic content to achieve this we ve started to develop a mentor matching scheme to pair startups with relevant advisors meanwhile we ve also developed a number of tools to share best practices around some of the steps almost all startups follow from raising funds to gaining the very first customers left widening the hub s reach screen shot 2016 10 27 at 2 13 12 pm today the hub is the largest startup recruitment site in denmark and we re now applying what we ve learned across the nordics launching hubs in norway and sweden opening up opportunities for cross country applications in markets where danske bank is most active v3rtoli33q0 '),
