 ('146', 'field', '15', 'en_us', ' this week industry thought leaders from incumbent banks and fintech startups gathered in the rainmaking loft for the first in the autumn season for the rainmaking sessions playing in the sandbox the session looked at the establishment of the regulatory sandbox run by the financial conduct authority and the appetite and capability of many incumbent banks to participate in the new scheme and partner with new entrants to the financial services landscape the outcome there are many footprints in the sandbox but many may have to wait some time for impressive castles to be built the fca s regulatory sandbox is meant to be a legal framework or a safe space where businesses can test innovative products services business models and delivery mechanisms this is a progressive step for startups in regulated industries like financial services however many young companies still need active partnerships with established banks firms and other corporates in order to test developing products with live data enterprise architecture and an active customer base sandboxes like the one set up by the fca in the uk are a step in the right direction for regulated industries but they struggle to be useful if certain startups aren t given the resources to test their products properly the fca sandbox was designed to allow for collaboration currently there are many fintech startups involved in the programme the fca does not make public the names or the number of startups participating in the sandbox however many of these companies still require participation from incumbent banks in order to adequately test their offerings in the safe legal framework the fca has established however many banks themselves are working on creating their own innovation labs to not only support and welcome new technology and services entrants but to enable and empower their own internal staff to embrace innovation many in this industry know that incumbent banks and financial services firms move at a pace considered much slower than is enjoyed in the silicon valley style startup world this is true even for banks that are working towards creating a more agile and flexible work environment the window of opportunity is open now to work within the fca regulatory sandbox this time around the pace of change and collaboration may be more missed connections than match com '),
