 ('211', 'field', '15', 'en_us', ' innovation is a bit of a messy word we might feel that we intrinsically grasp its meaning but how many of us can actually articulate what it means especially as it relates to our specific business innovation has increasingly become a marketing buzzword diluted by firms selling out of the box solutions to capitalize on what has become a blossoming hype curve we wanted to know how to better support our partners in the future and avoid falling into the tropes of others so we conducted a survey of over 80 participants from the rainmaking community that self identified as working in the corporate innovation management space the results are illuminating and worth sharing here s a sample of what the community said about innovation it is easy to see how the word innovation has become confused and abused responses ranged from bringing about sweeping visionary change all the way to solving a specific problem there s a lack of agreement on what the output of innovation should look like at first glance the responses can seem at odds we think this is actually to be expected closer inspection shows there are consistent themes there must be a positive change something done something createdthat change must be new sometimes iterative sometimes radical outcomes for innovation initiatives are defined based on their context in the specific market industry or organization it s very specific to your circumstances in summary the most important definition of innovation is your own innovation isin the eye of the beholder here s the current feeling about the innovation industry we loved the honesty the industry that supports your initiatives can be noisy and fragmented you re fighting to deliver against short and long term objectives battling for attention with your core business what you want is someone that is pragmatic in understanding your specific realities not traditional strategies from self proclaimed miracle workers from the feedback we received this quote really spoke to us we agree when you combine this with the breadth of responses on why innovation is important from keeping the lights on to delivering something tangible to improving the world it is clear that there can be a gap in getting from where you are today to where you d like to be the bridge that translates strategy into execution talk into action start with the biggest risk there are overlaps with these responses yet the top challenges are clear shifting mindsets placing focus on change and cultural adoption are the most glaringly consistent roadblocks in large organizations while we create resources to support you with more thoughts insights tools and frameworks to overcome these challenges here are a few interesting reads that will be helpful unlocking the benefits of self management without going all in on holacracy the culture deck how people work is as important as what they do five principles for building corporate innovation ecosystems why companies fail how to prevent it we also loved this curated list of summer 2016 things to read from the amazing first round a few years old now yet still relevant today top tips for building an innovation culture drive the surprising truth about what motivates us '),
